49
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,440
I’m going to kill you!

50
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:50,520
You’re going to be
out of our lives forever!

51
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:56,920
Mercaaaan!!!

52
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:10,480
It’s over.

53
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,840
She can’t do anything to you anymore.

54
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Are you okay?

55
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,560
Did she hurt you? Did
she do anything to you?

56
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,360
Thank God.

57
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,480
Thank God.

58
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,200
Thank God you’re okay.

59
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,160
Come on, let’s go inside.

60
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,840
Don’t think you’ve gotten away with this.

61
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,120
We’re going to settle accounts with you.

62
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,360
It’s over.

63
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,320
Slowly.

64
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:14,720
Because of you!

65
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,520
It’s over

66
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,400
I'll be right back.

67
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,200
I... I’m so sorry.

68
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,520
I only said those things in anger..

69
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,480
Ateş!

70
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,320
What happened?

71
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:47,440
There's no such thing...

72
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,400
Ateş, are you okay?

73
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,880
Please Ateş,

74
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,200
Shut up!

75
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,240
Pray that

76
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,080
Pray that you’re a woman,

77
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,360
otherwise I would’ve killed you.

78
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,376
It happened without me meaning it...

79
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,400
Don’t you dare

80
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,320
Don’t you dare make a fool out of me.

81
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,600
I heard everything!

82
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,680
That you shot Mercan,

83
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:23,000
that her kidnapping was your plan!

84
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,160
Everything!

85
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:35,600
These aren’t things you just say in anger!

86
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,000
You’re going to pay for this

87
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,720
And you’re going to pay dearly.

88
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:49,000
The monster we were looking for
was right under our noses, Cemal!

89
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:00,880
No.
No.

90
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,016
Please don’t look at me like that!

91
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,440
The hatred in your eyes hurts me so much.

92
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,040
Please

93
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,800
Ateş, please.

94
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:18,880
It’s all because of her.

95
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,680
If you hadn’t married her,

96
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,480
if you hadn’t loved her,
none of this would’ve happened.

97
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,440
I did everything because I love you.

98
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:41,880
What are you saying?

99
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,920
What kind of words are these?

100
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,840
I waited for you to love me.

101
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,280
You are my childhood.

102
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,440
My youth.

103
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,400
My future, my everything!

104
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,920
I waited for you to love me for years.

105
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:30,040
I watched as the man I loved fell in love
with someone else right before my eyes.

106
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,120
Enough!

107
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,800
You were my sister,

108
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,720
but now you’re not even that anymore.

109
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,440
I loved you so much, Ateş.

110
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,240
I told you to shut up!

111
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,360
Shut up!

112
00:07:58,560 --> 00:08:00,279
Ateş, please!

113
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,520
Nobody interfere.

114
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,040
Please

115
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:08,360
You’re sick!

116
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,000
Get out!

117
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,520
No! Please, don’t do this!

118
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,919
I did everything for you!

119
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,920
Go!

120
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,719
I loved you so much!

121
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:17,720
Move!

122
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,920
Ateş.

123
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,320
Ateş.

124
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,520
Ateş, stop

125
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,200
How could I have been this blind?

126
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:33,120
How could I not see what was
happening right in front of me?

127
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:39,000
He enemy was among us!

128
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,880
I still can’t believe it.

129
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:58,120
She tried to kill Mercan so many times!

130
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,800
What?

131
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,480
This woman tried to kill my daughter!

132
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:10,520
You took my son from me,

133
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,640
and now you were going to
take my daughter too, huh?

134
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,480
Mom!

135
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,440
Mom!

136
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,760
Stay away from my daughter!

137
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,120
Mother, Daughter?

138
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,880
Mom!

139
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,320
Ateş

140
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,840
calm down, son.

141
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,760
Look at the state my daughter is in.

142
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:30,320
Let’s understand what happened first.

143
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,080
What are you saying? Calm down?

144
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,560
What if something had happened to Mercan?

145
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,480
What if I had lost her?

146
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,280
Get her out of here!

147
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:58,320
I never want to see her again!

148
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,480
Get out of here!

149
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:05,880
What?

150
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,040
You’re not going to call the police?

151
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:12,280
You’re just going to let her walk away?

152
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:23,560
You said it yourself,
she tried to kill Mercan.

153
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:37,240
Why is justice served for
my son, but not for this girl?

154
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,240
Don’t you dare!

155
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,840
No one is calling the police!

156
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:51,280
I won’t let my daughter
rot in prison cells.

157
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:54,960
You poisoned my daughter
too. Now we’re even.

158
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,840
Is she just going to get away with?

159
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:00,280
How do we know she won’t try again?

160
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,560
This girl absolutely should
not be walking free on the streets

161
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,600
But yours got away with it, didn’t he?

162
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:23,000
I can never forgive someone who
tried to kill Mercan over and over!

163
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,976
If you hand my daughter over to the police,

164
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,640
I will never forgive you.

165
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,720
I will never forgive you. Never.

166
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:31,680
Don’t expect me to ignore what she’s done.

167
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,320
Ateş

168
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,880
You did everything you could to my Murat.

169
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:49,840
He died because of you.

170
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,120
If she tried to kill my daughter,

171
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,040
then she deserves to rot in prison.

172
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:58,920
Don’t compare my daughter
to your psychopath son.

173
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:05,120
Your son took the life of an innocent girl.

174
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:07,640
He walked around freely for years.

175
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:16,800
The evil your husband committed
is what made my daughter this way.

176
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,520
Enough!

177
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:21,440
Enough. Everyone needs to calm down.

178
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,800
None of your hands are clean.

179
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,480
None.

180
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,520
I wish

181
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,160
I wish you had competed in goodness

182
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:33,920
instead of evil.

183
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,240
Mercan Mother,

184
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:45,040
Let things settle down first.

185
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,440
We’ll decide what to do later.

186
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,480
Look at me!

187
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,000
There will be a price for what you’ve done.

188
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,440
Don’t think you’ve gotten away with it.

189
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,720
If you harmed Mercan,

190
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,680
you’ll face the consequences.

191
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,360
Mom!

192
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:25,360
- Mother Müzeyyen!
- Mother! Please open your eyes!

193
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:27,800
Mother Müzeyyen!

194
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,879
Mom!

195
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,200
- Mom! - Mother Müzeyyen!

196
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,440
Mother Müzeyyen, are you okay?

197
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,120
Mom!

198
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,400
Things got really messy again.

199
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,440
What happened, girl?

200
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:54,840
Ateş Bey threw Ms. Aslı out the front door.

201
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:57,960
I think it had something
to do with Ms. Mercan.

202
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,760
I think Ms. Aslı did something to her.

203
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:00,640
No way.

204
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,600
I didn’t say it, they did.

205
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,160
Good grief.

206
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:05,640
What could she have done?

207
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,640
I couldn’t make sense
of it. But it’s serious.

208
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:10,239
Mrs. Müzeyyen even fainted and all.

209
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:11,920
They’re talking about the police.

210
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:16,640
Oh, woe is me.

211
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:21,480
That Ms. Aslı always looked
like she was up to something.

212
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,640
Always staring at people so nastily.

213
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:25,880
Good grief.

214
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:29,120
Let’s wait and see, we’ll find out

215
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,880
Maybe Zehra knows.

216
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,760
I don't know.

217
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,320
But I mean..

218
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:38,800
I was going to share my good
news, and it got stuck in my throat.

219
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,000
Oh my dear.

220
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,160
May Almighty God help us.

221
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,600
May He finally smile upon my Tahir.

222
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:47,400
May He never separate him

223
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,440
from his Mercan.

224
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:53,560
May lovers never be separated
from the ones they love.

225
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,319
Never.

226
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:57,080
May God protect you

227
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:00,040
My dear.

228
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:03,160
I wish you could always sit right
by my side so I could protect you.

229
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:04,520
But whether you

230
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:07,760
go to the ends of the
earth or stay right here,

231
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:12,480
I’ll always be behind you, my child

232
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:13,800
Always.

233
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,760
But wherever you, no matter how far it is

234
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:21,040
If your head ever gets troubled,
if you ever feel overwhelmed,

235
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:25,480
just cry out “Mother” and
I’ll be by your side in an instant.

236
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:29,840
Thank you, dear mother.

237
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:34,080
I feel so lucky to have a mother like you.

238
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,560
I don’t know how I could ever repay you.

239
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,040
Be happy.

240
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:48,440
There’s no greater reward for a
mother than her child’s happiness.

241
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,440
What happened though?
Can’t really go and ask now.

242
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:01,720
Zehra would know though.

243
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,160
We'll ask her.

244
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,400
How are you, Mother Müzeyyen.

245
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:15,720
Feeling better?

246
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,240
Better.

247
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,120
Ateş,

248
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:24,760
Ateş, please don’t

249
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:28,160
Ateş, please don’t act as if
I don’t exist. I’m so sorry

250
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,600
Did you know about any of this?

251
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:33,960
No, I didn’t.

252
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:35,640
If I had known, I would have stopped it.

253
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,240
If Aslı has ended up like this,

254
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,440
it isn’t only her fault.

255
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,320
We bear responsibility too.

256
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:57,680
We fed that desire for revenge in her

257
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,920
with the things we said and did.

258
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,120
Those are not excuses.

259
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:02,880
We suffered a lot too

260
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:05,320
But we did not try to take innocent lives.

261
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:09,640
I’m asking you to forgive my daughter.

262
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:11,760
Don’t involve the police in this, son.

263
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:19,400
Aslı will pay for what she’s done!

264
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:28,840
And Mercan will decide what that price is.

265
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Period!

266
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,200
What?

267
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:37,680
Don’t let this one leave her room, Cemal!

268
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,960
Keep your eye on her at all times!

269
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:52,280
Are you pleased with yourself now?

270
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:55,440
How many times did I tell
you not to do anything crazy?

271
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:56,960
But who ever listens!

272
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:04,120
Well, here you are! Now
face the consequences!

273
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,840
Mom, please!

274
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,360
Please, Cemal!

275
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,719
Please do something!

276
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:12,240
I can’t survive in
prison. I’ll kill myself!

277
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:15,560
You should have thought of
that before things got this far.

278
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:21,440
Don’t be ungrateful!

279
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:24,720
I fed you, raised you!
I was a mother to you!

280
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:32,520
I won’t let you sacrifice my daughter
because of a murderer’s daughter!

281
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:38,160
Give me those images right now!

282
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:41,840
Without the video, no
one can prove anything.

283
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:45,440
Yes, you fed us and raised
us. I don’t deny that.

284
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:47,000
Thank you.

285
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:54,160
But you didn’t do it so we would
turn a blind eye to attempted murder.

286
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,760
I learned what is right from you too.

287
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,920
Ateş and Mercan

288
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,440
will decide.

289
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:14,480
I listened to you once and kept quiet.

290
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
I made a mistake.

291
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:17,280
But not again.

292
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:27,840
Don’t be afraid.

293
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,360
I will never let them
hand you over to the police.

294
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:34,160
Don’t be afraid.

295
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:49,840
So much happened right under
my nose and I had no idea.

296
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:55,119
How can someone I’ve known since
childhood, someone I called my sister,

297
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:56,120
do something like this!

298
00:19:58,680 --> 00:19:59,680
You’re right

299
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:01,640
it’s impossible to comprehend.

300
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,000
But

301
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:06,600
But I’m still trying to
understand her feelings.

302
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,480
What feelings, Mercan?!

303
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:12,160
That’s just an excuse she
found for the evil she did

304
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:15,240
We should have called the police.

305
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:18,080
Look,

306
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,440
I’m very angry too.

307
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,480
I nearly died because of her.

308
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:23,520
But

309
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:25,840
in the end she’s just a young girl.

310
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:30,360
I don’t even understand why I’m trying
to find excuses to be lenient with her.

311
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:33,000
Calling the police is the easiest thing.

312
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:36,320
But I want to be sure
I’m doing the right thing.

313
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:38,000
She doesn’t deserve your mercy!

314
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:41,720
She will answer for what she did!

315
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:43,920
That is the right thing!

316
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,200
Ateş

317
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,480
Please calm down a little.

318
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:50,800
Please.

319
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,440
I’m so sorry, Mercan.

320
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:06,400
For everything you went through.

321
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,240
I don’t understand how I didn’t
realize any of this while it was happening.

322
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,440
There were signs, actually.

323
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,000
Maybe I didn’t want to see them.

324
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:21,040
Or I didn't.

325
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,560
What happened to you is
partly my responsibility too.

326
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:31,920
I’m so sorry

327
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,000
For everything.

328
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,920
Please don’t blame yourself.

329
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,360
No one should carry the burden
of someone else’s crimes.

330
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,080
Everything will get better.

331
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:59,080
I’ll put everything
right for the two of us.

332
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:03,480
I need to talk to Cemal.

333
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:49,160
Mercan went through because of her!

334
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:52,079
Thinking about it drives me insane! f.

335
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:53,560
And most of all, I’m angry at myself.

336
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:57,040
We lived under the same roof as a monster

337
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,480
and never even sensed it.

338
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:04,520
What’s wrong with you? Cat got your tongue.

339
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:09,080
Forgive me, Ateş.

340
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:12,000
What happened, Cemal?
What am I forgiving you for?

341
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:15,560
It’s hard for me to say.

342
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:17,040
So..

343
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:19,480
Just,

344
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:20,800
Watch this

345
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:57,680
This..

346
00:23:58,920 --> 00:23:59,920
How..

347
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:04,960
When...

348
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:08,240
Did you know about this?

349
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:11,080
What happened today is my fault.

350
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:16,080
You knew and you hid it from me?!

351
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:20,080
Ateş!

352
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:21,919
You knew and you hid it from me!

353
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:23,240
I was going to tell you, I swear!

354
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:24,280
When?

355
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:27,160
I just found out

356
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,520
I was going to tell you, I swear!

357
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,120
You were my brother.

358
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:31,920
My closest friend.

359
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,800
I was going to tell you.

360
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,640
What were you waiting for!

361
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:42,000
For Mercan to die?!

362
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:43,280
I was torn, Ateş.

363
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,560
I gave in to my love.

364
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:54,920
Ateş

365
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,720
What are you doing?!

366
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:05,760
You would understand me best.

367
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,440
What love makes you do!

368
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:11,800
I love Aslı, Ateş.

369
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:15,840
My love grew inside me.

370
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:18,600
I couldn't tell anyone.

371
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:21,680
I shouted it to the
mountains and the stones.

372
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:23,520
No one knows better than you.

373
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:27,200
No one knows better than
you what can be done for love,

374
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:28,560
what can be given up for it.

375
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:32,360
Do you think it’s easy?

376
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:34,920
Do you think it's easy
what I've been through.

377
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:39,720
I couldn’t even look at her
face in case it would be understood.

378
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:45,120
When I learned what Aslı had done,
I didn’t know what to do, Ateş.

379
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:50,320
I wanted her to tell you herself.

380
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:53,480
She cried and begged.

381
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,640
I thought of Mother Müzeyyen.

382
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,920
I thought of us, our family.

383
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,640
I was torn between my loyalty
to you and to the family.

384
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:06,880
I wanted our family not to fall apart.

385
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:10,200
I made a terrible mistake.

386
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:12,040
A huge mistake.

387
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:13,800
I know.

388
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,680
Whatever you do to me,

389
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:20,480
you're right.

390
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:25,280
I couldn’t gather the courage to say it.

391
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:28,200
I was afraid.

392
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:33,680
I’m so sorry, Mercan.

393
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,040
I never wanted it to be like this.

394
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:22,880
No.

395
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,680
No! No way! I can’t go to prison!

396
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,960
Not because of that girl!

397
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:30,560
I can’t leave Ateş to her!

398
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:33,480
I have to find a solution!

399
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:37,920
But what!

400
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,960
Think! Think! Think!

401
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:42,920
Use your head!

402
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,480
You’ve overcome so much!

403
00:27:46,520 --> 00:27:47,640
You can get out of this too!

404
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,680
I have to find a solution! But what!

405
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,200
I found it!

406
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:14,920
Nezir.

407
00:28:15,640 --> 00:28:17,080
We’re in serious trouble

408
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:18,560
Everything has come out.

409
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:20,760
How?

410
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:22,640
What do you mean?

411
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,720
Ateş found out

412
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:26,640
what I did to Mercan.

413
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:29,160
He’s going to report me to the police.

414
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:33,120
Do they know we worked together?

415
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:36,240
No, they don’t know.

416
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,440
You have to help me, Nezir.

417
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:41,800
I’m sorry.

418
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:43,560
I can’t help you.

419
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:46,160
You have to!

420
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,120
You will, Nezir.

421
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:53,680
Otherwise I’ll tell Mercan
that you knew everything too.

422
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,640
That I shot her,

423
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:58,600
and you protected me.

424
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,120
I'm not bluffing.

425
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:02,600
I’ll tell her

426
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,560
Because I have nothing
left to lose anymore.

427
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:12,520
What do you want?

428
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:16,360
If they report me to the police,

429
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:18,200
I’ll have to run away.

430
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:20,680
I need your help for that.

431
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:24,200
I want you to make the necessary
arrangements in advance just in case.

432
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:26,800
I’ll call you later.

433
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:28,960
Wait for me to call you.

434
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:35,400
That Aslı.

435
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:38,920
That Aslı.

436
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:48,680
You got this, Mother.

437
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:49,960
A little bit more.

438
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:51,960
Throw it up.

439
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:54,440
Like this?

440
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:00,800
You got this Mother.

441
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:03,200
Italians do this better.

442
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:05,640
Well,

443
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:08,000
I heard that Ms. Aslı
tried to kill Ms. Mercan.

444
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:09,040
That’s all I heard.
What?

445
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:12,256
That’s what I heard, honestly.

446
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,520
Where is the flaxseed?

447
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,160
Dear God.

448
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:20,960
Ms. Çiçek supposedly organized this pantry.

449
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:22,280
What kind of organizing is this?

450
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:23,920
Everything’s all mixed up.

451
00:30:27,120 --> 00:30:30,200
The whole place is in chaos, and
all she cares about is flaxseed.

452
00:30:35,080 --> 00:30:36,000
Here, darling.

453
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:37,440
Your flaxseed.

454
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,360
See how I found it instantly?

455
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,880
Maybe the problem is yo

456
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,840
Maybe your eyes are
spinning too fast to see it.

457
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:49,320
So

458
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:50,880
What’s going to happen now?

459
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:54,920
I don’t know. But they’re
talking about police and all that.

460
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:57,600
Oh dear, oh dear.

461
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:03,760
My God.

462
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:06,120
In this mansion

463
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:07,960
There’s never a lack of action

464
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,520
My heart tightened, honestly.

465
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,160
Same.

466
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:13,880
Do you know what happened?

467
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:17,760
Mr. Ateş and Mr. Cemal
got into a fistfight.

468
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:18,840
What?
Oh wow.

469
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:20,200
Yeah.

470
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:21,520
That was big.

471
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:24,400
Oh wow.

472
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,880
Why? What happened? They’re like brothers.

473
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:32,480
We couldn’t make sense of it.

474
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,480
Dear God.

475
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:40,680
So when is your wedding, Çiçek?

476
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,960
We should start looking
at dresses and things.

477
00:31:49,280 --> 00:31:50,280
What?

478
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:51,680
What happened?

479
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,200
Why are you all looking at me like that?

480
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:55,320
Did I say something wrong?

481
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:58,760
We didn’t have a wedding, so I figured
maybe they would, that’s all I asked.

482
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:03,080
Dear God.

483
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:05,136
The sensible ones never find me,

484
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,720
but the crazy ones never leave my side.

485
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:11,320
Come on, everyone, back to work.

486
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:13,720
You found your flaxseed, right?

487
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:16,640
Now take it, go to the
mansion. Handle there.

488
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:18,600
Don't you have anything to do?

489
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:20,440
We do, Aunt Binnaz.

490
00:32:20,520 --> 00:32:21,920
Then, good luck everyone.

491
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:23,560
We have works to do.

492
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:24,840
Don't hold us.

493
00:32:31,560 --> 00:32:32,560
Berat!
Yes!

494
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:33,840
Don't you have anything to do?

495
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,600
I do, I'll go.

496
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:36,800
Go then.

497
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,160
Help?

498
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:40,640
No.

499
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:45,760
You'll put this back, right dear?

500
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,000
Berat, go away already!

501
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:57,240
Alright then.
Wait.

502
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,240
Put this back too.

503
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:04,320
Zehra!

504
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:07,120
Too bad, he missed his wife.

505
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,280
Flaxseed!

506
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:12,280
How's it?

507
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:14,720
Go.
God!

508
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:16,800
I couldn't!
You will.

509
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:20,360
Look how many I did. One
of them will eventually.

510
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:22,280
Well.

511
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:24,240
It's like the chef's doing.

512
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:25,000
Not like this.

513
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,720
You'll put this here

514
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:31,320
None of them equals you, Mother!

515
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:33,320
Of course!

516
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:41,200
That's it.

517
