527
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:29,760
I’ve never been so wrong
about a person in my entire life.

528
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:31,840
We grew up together.

529
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,280
Ou have every right to be shocked.

530
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:37,680
But I’m not as shocked as you are.

531
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:41,320
Because she showed me
her ugly side many times.

532
00:34:43,040 --> 00:34:44,040
I think

533
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:47,480
she avoided showing you her
dark side because she loved you.

534
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:50,520
But if you ask whether I
expected it to go this far,

535
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:52,920
no,

536
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:54,320
I didn’t.

537
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:56,360
The fault is mine.

538
00:34:56,640 --> 00:34:57,640
Mine!

539
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:01,760
Ateş!

540
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:03,360
Ateş! Stop!

541
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:05,000
You’re going to hurt yourself!

542
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:06,440
Look,

543
00:35:08,200 --> 00:35:09,160
I’m very angry too.

544
00:35:09,161 --> 00:35:10,841
But not like this, not by smashing things.

545
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:12,800
What did you go through, Mercan?

546
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:15,280
She’s responsible for
all the pain you suffered.

547
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:18,840
And most of all, I am.

548
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:22,800
I will never forgive myself.

549
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:25,240
Don’t think like that.

550
00:35:27,040 --> 00:35:28,760
That girl cannot go unpunished

551
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:32,521
When I started down this road, I
thought I had calculated everything.

552
00:35:36,080 --> 00:35:38,256
But it never even crossed my
mind that I would be betrayed

553
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:39,920
by the people I loved most.

554
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:44,200
I was stabbed in the back.

555
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:49,000
I don’t think what Cemal did was betrayal.

556
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:53,120
He was torn between his
love and his conscience.

557
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:03,560
Love won.

558
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,440
That doesn’t make him a traitor.

559
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:11,080
Whoever does wrong will
pay for it, no matter what!

560
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:44,320
May God give everyone a good child.

561
00:36:45,480 --> 00:36:47,280
That’s what you used
to say to me, wasn’t it?

562
00:36:48,200 --> 00:36:49,640
Murderer’s mother.

563
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:51,320
Shut your mouth!

564
00:36:57,520 --> 00:36:59,520
People used to say it,
but I wouldn’t believe it.

565
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:03,480
What people go through
really does change them.

566
00:37:05,560 --> 00:37:08,400
When you first came to this mansion,
I thought you were something else.

567
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:11,240
Now I see

568
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:13,120
I thought too highly of you.

569
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:18,200
I came here to make you pay, Mrs. Nermin

570
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:21,160
And I won’t leave before you do.

571
00:37:22,560 --> 00:37:24,280
But now you’re the one paying.

572
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:26,880
Through the one you love most

573
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:29,320
your child.

574
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,440
Ladies. Please.

575
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:34,360
What are you doing?

576
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:37,680
Mrs. Nermin. Maybe you should go
to your room before this gets worse?

577
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,160
Mrs. Müzeyyen, this way..

578
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,640
I don’t need you telling me what to do.

579
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:43,560
I was leaving already!

580
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:47,200
I’m not eager to look at
this woman’s face either.

581
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:56,640
Don’t ever interfere in my business again!

582
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:00,360
Alright.

583
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:02,480
Where is Ateş?

584
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:05,040
I’m waiting to speak to him.

585
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,080
He was in the garden with Mercan.

586
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:17,080
How am I going to convince Ateş?

587
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:25,040
Maybe the person who needs
persuading isn’t Ateş after all.

588
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:53,560
I came to see Mercan

589
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:57,000
What happened to you?

590
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:03,160
You wouldn’t want to know.

591
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:08,320
If you’ll excuse me,
I’m going to go for a walk.

592
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:09,520
No.

593
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:13,120
You’re not going
anywhere until you tell me.

594
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:16,200
I made a mistake.

595
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:18,440
A very big one.

596
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:25,760
Which of us doesn’t make mistakes?

597
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:29,640
This isn’t

598
00:39:30,520 --> 00:39:32,360
something that can be
brushed aside like that.

599
00:39:34,120 --> 00:39:35,880
I wronged Ateş.

600
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,160
Haydar

601
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:02,480
why are you so quiet?

602
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:04,200
What’s going through your mind?

603
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:07,880
I’m thinking about

604
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:10,520
ow we can turn this Aslı
matter to our advantage.

605
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:17,400
Ateş said he would decide her punishment.

606
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:24,520
How is Mercan?

607
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:27,360
How would she be?

608
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:29,960
She’s in great shock, of course.

609
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:34,080
I don’t think she’ll recover
from its effects for a long time.

610
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:37,880
I’ll support her.

611
00:40:43,640 --> 00:40:44,640
Good.

612
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,600
Good. Take care of your sister.

613
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:52,080
We’ll drive the Karahans away

614
00:40:53,080 --> 00:40:54,520
We’ll be a family again.

615
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:00,400
Keep me informed of developments.

616
00:41:01,120 --> 00:41:03,160
I want to know everything
happening in the mansion.

617
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:19,240
Your nose is red.

618
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:20,360
Shall we go inside?

619
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:22,080
No,

620
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:23,560
I’m perfectly fine like this.

621
00:41:24,360 --> 00:41:25,920
Are you cold? Shall we go inside?

622
00:41:27,080 --> 00:41:28,240
Let’s not.

623
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:31,520
Let’s stay a little longer

624
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:33,920
The inside suffocates me.

625
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:36,760
What we’ve been through is terrible,

626
00:41:37,080 --> 00:41:39,040
but despite everything,
we’re side by side again.

627
00:41:41,840 --> 00:41:43,320
That’s what gives me strength.

628
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:49,400
Every time we say “this time it’s over,”

629
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:52,520
we wake up to a new nightmare.

630
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:55,400
It feels like it’s never going to end.

631
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:01,880
Maybe we can chase the
nightmares away together.

632
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:06,760
You chase one away and another comes.

633
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:13,440
These days will pass

634
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:15,120
Look at all we’ve survived.

635
00:42:16,880 --> 00:42:17,960
But despite everything,

636
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:19,800
we’re side by side again.

637
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:35,200
What’s wrong with you?

638
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:38,160
Nothing.

639
00:42:40,760 --> 00:42:42,560
Of course this affected you.

640
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:43,720
That’s normal.

641
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:46,640
By tomorrow you’ll feel better.

642
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:49,600
We can do something tomorrow if you want.

643
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:51,200
Ride bikes again.

644
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:53,600
You’ve probably forgotten by now.

645
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:06,880
Tomorrow is the court hearing.

646
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:13,880
Mercan... I know this is a very bad time
to talk about it, but me divorcing you-

647
00:43:20,840 --> 00:43:22,360
Let’s not talk about that now, okay?

648
00:44:06,960 --> 00:44:09,560
Never warmed to Aslı anyway

649
00:44:10,480 --> 00:44:13,640
But I still can’t understand
how she could be this cruel.

650
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:15,640
The fact that

651
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:18,080
she’s trying to justify
what she did with love

652
00:44:19,520 --> 00:44:20,760
makes it even more horrifying.

653
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:27,880
I know how sorry you are.

654
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:32,320
And I know you would want me to be honest.

655
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:36,520
The moment you learned
about this, not telling Ateş

656
00:44:37,320 --> 00:44:38,760
was a huge mistake.

657
00:44:42,360 --> 00:44:43,400
I know it was a mistake.

658
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:48,120
The bridges are burned now.

659
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:51,600
Those bridges don’t burn so easily.

660
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:54,120
They just need time.

661
00:44:56,480 --> 00:44:58,520
It’ll be hard for him to trust me now.

662
00:45:00,920 --> 00:45:02,200
What I did

663
00:45:02,440 --> 00:45:03,960
can't be forgiven.

664
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:10,880
I don't know

665
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:14,760
if he forgives me.

666
00:45:30,920 --> 00:45:32,840
Can I speak to you for a moment?

667
00:45:34,600 --> 00:45:35,840
There’s nothing to talk about!

668
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:40,000
Ateş,

669
00:45:41,160 --> 00:45:42,160
calm down.

670
00:45:43,680 --> 00:45:44,960
I can talk to her. It’s fine.

671
00:45:47,080 --> 00:45:48,080
Fine.

672
00:45:48,960 --> 00:45:50,200
But I’m staying with you.

673
00:45:52,920 --> 00:45:54,040
There’s no need.

674
00:45:57,320 --> 00:45:58,320
Please.

675
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:12,520
You probably know that I don’t
love you even as much as my sins.

676
00:46:13,520 --> 00:46:14,800
I know very well.

677
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:16,440
And

678
00:46:16,920 --> 00:46:19,560
I’m proud of myself for not being loved

679
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:21,160
by someone like you.

680
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:23,240
I wonder

681
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:26,040
are you proud of your murderer father too?

682
00:46:27,440 --> 00:46:31,120
That man did so much evil and
never spent even a day in prison.

683
00:46:32,520 --> 00:46:34,560
So why should my daughter go to prison?

684
00:46:36,360 --> 00:46:39,080
I know all of this is because of my father.

685
00:46:41,080 --> 00:46:43,560
Ever since you came to this
mansion, you kept tormenting me.

686
00:46:44,920 --> 00:46:46,680
You tried to humiliate me.

687
00:46:47,320 --> 00:46:48,480
You hurt me

688
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:51,280
You tried to slander me

689
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:54,120
Even though

690
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:56,480
I didn’t understand why back then

691
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:57,800
I stayed silent

692
00:46:58,200 --> 00:46:59,480
I never disrespected you,

693
00:47:00,760 --> 00:47:02,280
because you were older than me.

694
00:47:03,720 --> 00:47:04,360
Now

695
00:47:04,680 --> 00:47:06,880
I know why you did those things.

696
00:47:12,040 --> 00:47:13,960
Because I knew nothing about any of it.

697
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:17,400
You made me pay for my father’s sins.

698
00:47:18,720 --> 00:47:20,480
I do not deserve what you put me through.

699
00:47:23,200 --> 00:47:25,560
My daughter doesn’t deserve prison either.

700
00:47:27,440 --> 00:47:28,760
Because what she lived through,

701
00:47:29,720 --> 00:47:31,920
the pain she endured,
destroyed her balance.

702
00:47:32,400 --> 00:47:33,480
Her anger is immense

703
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:37,880
Everyone has a share in
that. Most of all, your father.

704
00:47:41,120 --> 00:47:43,080
If my daughter goes to prison,

705
00:47:43,960 --> 00:47:47,120
know this: that fire of
revenge will never go out.

706
00:47:48,960 --> 00:47:52,200
I want this hatred to end, I want
that fire of revenge to die out.

707
00:47:54,040 --> 00:47:55,880
But I’m not afraid of your threats either.

708
00:47:56,680 --> 00:47:57,800
You should know that too.

709
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:03,880
Maybe when a person has
nearly died many times,

710
00:48:04,880 --> 00:48:06,280
she becomes more fearless.

711
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:23,640
Honestly,

712
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:28,000
every time I think about
it, my blood runs cold.

713
00:48:29,120 --> 00:48:30,720
So much happened right under our noses

714
00:48:31,160 --> 00:48:32,280
and we never sensed a thing.

715
00:48:33,360 --> 00:48:34,360
Yo know what?

716
00:48:34,840 --> 00:48:36,040
The woman is literally insane.

717
00:48:36,760 --> 00:48:37,760
That's it.

718
00:48:38,520 --> 00:48:41,360
I never liked Ms. Aslı
from the very beginning.

719
00:48:41,480 --> 00:48:42,639
She was too rough,

720
00:48:42,640 --> 00:48:43,800
too sly.

721
00:48:45,200 --> 00:48:47,920
But with your clever wife’s sharp mind,

722
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:50,160
the moment I first looked
at her face, I understood it.

723
00:48:50,560 --> 00:48:52,400
That’s why I always
kept my distance from her.

724
00:48:54,920 --> 00:48:56,000
Dear wife, I..

725
00:48:57,520 --> 00:48:58,520
Don't get it.

726
00:48:58,680 --> 00:49:00,520
These rich people are something else.

727
00:49:01,520 --> 00:49:02,880
I mean, you’ve got all that money.

728
00:49:03,680 --> 00:49:05,160
Eat, drink, travel.

729
00:49:05,680 --> 00:49:06,680
Right?

730
00:49:06,840 --> 00:49:08,240
But no, comfort bothers people.

731
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:09,520
It bothers.

732
00:49:10,120 --> 00:49:12,280
Because for the rich, evil is free.

733
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:13,400
Got it?

734
00:49:13,720 --> 00:49:15,120
They never pay the price.

735
00:49:15,640 --> 00:49:18,240
They always find a way to cover it up.

736
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:22,480
But you know,

737
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:25,200
I think the real fault
lies with her mother.

738
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:28,320
What kind of child did she raise?

739
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:30,000
Right?

740
00:49:34,120 --> 00:49:35,120
My dear wife.

741
00:49:36,280 --> 00:49:38,640
Our children won’t be like that.

742
00:49:39,240 --> 00:49:41,960
We’ll teach them love and goodness.

743
00:49:42,320 --> 00:49:43,320
Okay?

744
00:49:57,880 --> 00:49:58,920
Yes, mother?

745
00:49:59,680 --> 00:50:00,560
Berat,

746
00:50:00,600 --> 00:50:01,840
son, where are you?

747
00:50:02,320 --> 00:50:03,320
Why are you asking?

748
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:06,200
You’re hiding somewhere
slacking off again, aren’t you?

749
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:09,760
Stop loafing around and get back
to work. Don’t make me look bad.

750
00:50:11,320 --> 00:50:12,360
Okay, mother.

751
00:50:12,600 --> 00:50:13,200
Okay

752
00:50:13,440 --> 00:50:14,440
Hang up.

753
00:50:20,520 --> 00:50:21,799
What was I saying?

754
00:50:21,800 --> 00:50:22,800
Ah,

755
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:25,480
we were talking about
our children, weren’t we?

756
00:50:26,280 --> 00:50:28,680
Forget children for now

757
00:50:28,760 --> 00:50:29,560
Get up and go.

758
00:50:29,720 --> 00:50:31,800
Don’t drive your mother crazy.

759
00:50:32,320 --> 00:50:33,320
Go.

760
00:50:35,480 --> 00:50:36,480
You’re right,

761
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:40,480
We’ll talk later.

762
00:50:57,360 --> 00:50:58,360
Mercan

763
00:51:00,720 --> 00:51:02,160
Why are you outside in this cold?

764
00:51:02,720 --> 00:51:03,720
Is everything all right?

765
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:09,160
There’s something I want
to talk to you about, Ateş.

766
00:51:10,080 --> 00:51:11,120
Let’s talk.

767
00:51:15,560 --> 00:51:16,880
I’ve thought a lot

768
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:21,960
Go ahead, answer it.

769
00:51:23,400 --> 00:51:24,520
Hello, Ms. Zahide

770
00:51:26,960 --> 00:51:29,440
Yes, I read the reports. I
made one or two corrections.

771
00:51:30,280 --> 00:51:31,280
I’ll email them to you.

772
00:51:33,440 --> 00:51:34,440
You need it right away?

773
00:51:36,240 --> 00:51:37,480
You take care of your work.

774
00:51:37,560 --> 00:51:38,800
Don’t worry about me.

775
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:42,200
Fine

776
00:51:54,600 --> 00:51:55,600
My daughter!

777
00:52:06,280 --> 00:52:08,280
When I heard what
happened, I was horrified.

778
00:52:09,240 --> 00:52:11,200
I was so worried about you.

779
00:52:14,240 --> 00:52:17,520
I tormented myself for falling into
the hands of these unstable people.

780
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:18,880
Father.

781
00:52:18,920 --> 00:52:20,480
Thank goodness you’ll be divorced soon.

782
00:52:21,080 --> 00:52:22,320
We’ll be rid of all this.

783
00:52:24,960 --> 00:52:26,840
You were my hero, Father.

784
00:52:28,360 --> 00:52:31,760
I would do anything to make you love me.

785
00:52:32,840 --> 00:52:34,080
I tried to.

786
00:52:35,400 --> 00:52:37,320
Because Mother didn’t love me.

787
00:52:37,800 --> 00:52:39,080
She had Murat

788
00:52:41,760 --> 00:52:43,920
I thought you loved me.

789
00:52:45,880 --> 00:52:47,480
But actually, you never loved me either.

790
00:52:51,640 --> 00:52:53,320
Let me ask you something.

791
00:52:55,040 --> 00:52:57,320
Did you ever wonder how I felt?

792
00:52:58,840 --> 00:53:00,640
I don’t understand what
you’re trying to say.

793
00:53:01,800 --> 00:53:02,800
All this time...

794
00:53:03,880 --> 00:53:05,680
when you threw me in front of Nezir,

795
00:53:06,640 --> 00:53:08,280
when you made me marry Ateş,

796
00:53:09,040 --> 00:53:11,480
now that I’m about to divorce him...

797
00:53:11,920 --> 00:53:15,920
did you ever ask what I think, what I want?

798
00:53:18,840 --> 00:53:20,120
I loved Ateş very much, Father.

799
00:53:21,440 --> 00:53:22,760
And he loved me.

800
00:53:24,560 --> 00:53:26,200
But we could never be happy.

801
00:53:27,680 --> 00:53:28,680
Because of you

802
00:53:32,440 --> 00:53:36,360
Every pain we lived, every
disaster, happened because of you.

803
00:53:38,560 --> 00:53:40,120
You destroyed families.

804
00:53:41,160 --> 00:53:43,400
You tormented two children for days.

805
00:53:43,960 --> 00:53:44,960
You ..

806
00:53:45,360 --> 00:53:47,320
You caused one of them to die.

807
00:53:47,680 --> 00:53:48,680
Don’t

808
00:53:49,240 --> 00:53:51,760
Don’t you dare tell me you did it for me

809
00:53:54,560 --> 00:53:56,720
Ateş has poisoned you again.

810
00:53:59,040 --> 00:54:01,080
Ateş didn’t poison me.

811
00:54:02,360 --> 00:54:05,000
Ateş made me face the
true face of my family.

812
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:14,160
Why can’t you admit fault even once?

813
00:54:16,480 --> 00:54:19,240
When I look at your face, I don’t
see the slightest sign of regret.

814
00:54:20,280 --> 00:54:21,800
Do you have no conscience at all?

815
00:54:24,520 --> 00:54:26,520
Everywhere I turn, there’s anger

816
00:54:26,640 --> 00:54:27,720
and hatred.

817
00:54:28,720 --> 00:54:29,720
You on one side

818
00:54:30,120 --> 00:54:32,000
Müzeyyen Hanım and Aslı on the other.

819
00:54:34,720 --> 00:54:38,120
You have no idea how much damage you
and your families have done to people.

820
00:54:39,440 --> 00:54:40,600
Or worse

821
00:54:41,440 --> 00:54:42,840
you just don’t care

822
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:46,600
Because of you, no one is happy.

823
00:54:47,120 --> 00:54:48,120
And no one ever will be.

824
00:54:49,520 --> 00:54:53,520
With your never-ending hatred,
you have condemned us to unhappiness.

825
00:55:29,040 --> 00:55:31,760
Would you like some more dessert, my love?

826
00:55:31,840 --> 00:55:32,920
No, dear.

827
00:55:33,360 --> 00:55:34,719
I’m stuffed up to here.

828
00:55:34,720 --> 00:55:36,039
It was so delicious

829
00:55:36,040 --> 00:55:37,240
I lost control and overdid it.

830
00:55:38,200 --> 00:55:39,480
Bless your hands

831
00:55:42,200 --> 00:55:43,280
Enjoy it

832
00:55:45,800 --> 00:55:46,800
By the way,

833
00:55:47,280 --> 00:55:49,416
Will you make desserts for
me after we get married too?

834
00:55:49,440 --> 00:55:51,240
You promised.

835
00:55:51,280 --> 00:55:52,800
Of course I will.

836
00:55:53,880 --> 00:55:57,440
The desserts and dishes you love
will never be missing from our home.

837
00:55:57,480 --> 00:55:58,840
I’ll take good care of my husband.

838
00:55:59,320 --> 00:56:00,320
You say so.

839
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:06,480
Since cooking and dessert
are your department,

840
00:56:06,840 --> 00:56:10,760
then I’ll prepare breakfast.

841
00:56:11,040 --> 00:56:12,040
To my love.

842
00:56:12,760 --> 00:56:14,960
I don’t want my beautiful wife to get tired

843
00:56:17,840 --> 00:56:21,080
Besides, you don’t like waking up early.

844
00:56:21,520 --> 00:56:25,760
I don’t know if you realize it, but
you’re like a sleepwalker in the mornings.

845
00:56:26,760 --> 00:56:29,600
And in the evenings, you nod off
sitting where you are like an old man.

846
00:56:29,760 --> 00:56:30,520
Old man?

847
00:56:30,560 --> 00:56:33,640
Your head droops to the side. I
laugh so much when I see you like that.

848
00:56:34,360 --> 00:56:36,600
If I can make you laugh,
that’s enough to make me happy.

849
00:56:37,360 --> 00:56:40,000
Let’s always laugh like
this. Let’s always be happy.

850
00:56:52,080 --> 00:56:54,600
I should get back to work.

851
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:57,440
Otherwise the food won’t be ready on time.

852
00:56:57,720 --> 00:56:59,000
Yeah, work.

853
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:22,960
Wait.

854
00:57:37,720 --> 00:57:38,920
I promise you.

855
00:57:40,360 --> 00:57:42,560
I will never let go of this
hand for as long as I live.

856
00:58:26,400 --> 00:58:29,120
I didn’t get the chance to ask in
the garden because the phone rang.

857
00:58:29,240 --> 00:58:30,600
You said you wanted to talk to me?

858
00:58:31,000 --> 00:58:32,120
Yes, I do.

859
00:58:32,880 --> 00:58:33,880
What is it?

860
00:58:34,680 --> 00:58:36,640
Did Mother Müzeyyen say
something that upset you?

861
00:58:36,880 --> 00:58:37,880
No.

862
00:58:38,480 --> 00:58:40,960
I don’t care about her, and I
don’t care what happens to Aslı.

863
00:58:43,240 --> 00:58:46,760
I don’t want to live with
revenge, hatred, and evil.

864
00:58:48,680 --> 00:58:50,400
And we’ve suffered so much because of them.

865
00:58:51,160 --> 00:58:52,880
I don’t want this to go on like this.

866
00:58:54,840 --> 00:58:57,680
I don’t know what to do or how to cope.

867
00:58:58,480 --> 00:58:59,720
I want it to end.

868
00:59:04,040 --> 00:59:05,480
I will not forgive Aslı.

869
00:59:06,800 --> 00:59:08,600
But I’m not going to press charges either.

870
00:59:08,760 --> 00:59:10,720
And I want you not to drag this out either.

871
00:59:12,360 --> 00:59:13,360
Are you sure?

872
00:59:14,240 --> 00:59:15,240
I am.

873
00:59:15,640 --> 00:59:17,320
I thought about it, and I made a decision.

874
00:59:18,680 --> 00:59:20,040
I will not let this hatred

875
00:59:20,720 --> 00:59:22,640
and desire for revenge infect me too.

876
00:59:25,840 --> 00:59:26,840
Come with me.
Where?

877
00:59:27,920 --> 00:59:28,920
We need to talk.

878
00:59:29,560 --> 00:59:30,560
All right.

879
00:59:30,960 --> 00:59:33,120
We’ll talk later, but
this can’t wait any longer.

880
00:59:33,720 --> 00:59:35,000
There’s something we need to do.

881
00:59:35,120 --> 00:59:36,120
Come

882
00:59:48,440 --> 00:59:49,440
What’s going on?

883
00:59:49,760 --> 00:59:50,880
Why did you call us here?

884
00:59:57,840 --> 00:59:59,200
Now that we’re all gathered,

885
00:59:59,960 --> 01:00:01,280
I can explain.

886
01:00:06,480 --> 01:00:08,400
Mercan will not press charges against Aslı.

887
01:00:15,440 --> 01:00:16,440
That is

888
01:00:16,760 --> 01:00:17,800
Mercan’s decision.

889
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:24,040
But I do not agree with her.

890
01:00:35,320 --> 01:00:37,480
Because I believe Aslı should
pay for what she’s done.

891
01:00:42,960 --> 01:00:44,240
So I called the police.

892
01:00:50,520 --> 01:00:52,440
Ateş! How can you do this?!

893
01:00:55,520 --> 01:00:56,799
No, no, no!

894
01:00:56,800 --> 01:01:00,800
Ateş, please have mercy on me!
Forgive me, please forgive me!

895
01:01:00,840 --> 01:01:02,320
Please!

896
01:01:02,760 --> 01:01:03,760
Please!

897
01:01:03,960 --> 01:01:05,360
I won’t forgive you

898
01:01:12,480 --> 01:01:14,880
Because you have done such terrible things

899
01:01:18,840 --> 01:01:20,480
that you do not deserve forgiveness.

900
01:01:31,920 --> 01:01:32,920
Burak,

901
01:01:33,640 --> 01:01:34,640
would you open the door?

902
01:01:34,680 --> 01:01:36,000
No, no, no! Please!

903
01:01:36,040 --> 01:01:36,720
It must be the police.

904
01:01:36,721 --> 01:01:39,120
Please, mom!, Mom, please do something!

905
01:01:39,160 --> 01:01:42,720
Don’t hand me over. I
can’t survive in there. Cemal!

906
01:01:46,240 --> 01:01:47,400
Hello, good evening.

907
01:01:55,920 --> 01:01:57,280
Which one of you is Aslı Taner?

908
01:02:09,080 --> 01:02:10,080
I am.

909
01:02:17,600 --> 01:02:19,640
You need to come to the station with us.

910
01:02:22,160 --> 01:02:23,280
Don’t be upset, my daughter.

911
01:02:23,480 --> 01:02:25,120
I will never let you stay in that hole!

912
01:02:25,480 --> 01:02:27,640
I’ll find a way and save you,

913
01:02:28,320 --> 01:02:31,160
And I will never forgive
those who did this to you.

914
01:02:31,200 --> 01:02:32,000
We need to go.

915
01:02:32,040 --> 01:02:35,440
Mother, please save me. Ateş!

916
01:02:35,480 --> 01:02:37,640
Please, Cemal!

917
01:02:37,920 --> 01:02:41,879
Mother, please save me. Ateş!

918
01:02:41,880 --> 01:02:44,720
Mother do something!

919
01:02:44,760 --> 01:02:47,119
Mom!

920
01:02:47,120 --> 01:02:49,800
As you sow, so shall you reap.

921
01:02:50,280 --> 01:02:52,440
- Excuse us, please. - Mother!

922
01:02:52,480 --> 01:02:53,320
Please.

923
01:02:53,360 --> 01:02:54,520
Mom!

924
01:02:55,520 --> 01:02:56,840
Why did you do that?

925
01:02:58,760 --> 01:02:59,760
For justice.

926
01:03:05,200 --> 01:03:06,760
What I thought about your father,

927
01:03:09,120 --> 01:03:11,080
Even if the wrongdoer is part of my family

928
01:03:15,240 --> 01:03:16,400
there has to be justice.

929
01:03:30,160 --> 01:03:32,000
Oh, mom.

930
01:03:32,360 --> 01:03:33,360
What is it?

931
01:03:33,600 --> 01:03:34,920
I overdid it again.

932
01:03:40,440 --> 01:03:41,400
Too much

933
01:03:41,401 --> 01:03:43,600
You lose yourself whenever you see food.

934
01:03:43,880 --> 01:03:44,960
Yeah

935
01:03:45,960 --> 01:03:47,680
No place for even tea.

936
01:03:49,040 --> 01:03:49,840
I overdid it

937
01:03:50,040 --> 01:03:51,320
Too much.

938
01:03:53,560 --> 01:03:54,800
Not again.

939
01:03:55,480 --> 01:03:57,520
May it be sweet and
nourishing for my dear husband.

940
01:03:57,560 --> 01:03:59,040
Thanks, love.

941
01:04:04,720 --> 01:04:05,960
Thanks.

942
01:04:13,280 --> 01:04:14,840
Take it for me.

943
01:04:15,720 --> 01:04:16,720
Took it.

944
01:04:17,880 --> 01:04:18,920
Here.

945
01:04:19,480 --> 01:04:20,480
Take it.

946
01:04:21,600 --> 01:04:22,720
You did great, bride.

947
01:04:23,520 --> 01:04:27,240
After a meal like this,
all a man can do is lie down.

948
01:04:27,560 --> 01:04:29,400
Oh yes, all you do is lie down

949
01:04:29,600 --> 01:04:31,440
Watermelons grow by lying around too.

950
01:04:35,920 --> 01:04:37,120
What is it now, mother?

951
01:04:38,080 --> 01:04:39,560
What do you mean, what is it?

952
01:04:39,840 --> 01:04:41,880
Tomorrow they’re coming
to ask for the girl’s hand.

953
01:04:42,040 --> 01:04:46,280
There’s so much to do. Cleaning,
shopping, preparing treats

954
01:04:46,320 --> 01:04:47,920
There’s so much to do

955
01:04:49,080 --> 01:04:50,680
We’ll handle it, mother.

956
01:04:52,800 --> 01:04:53,800
Not such a huge ordeal

957
01:04:54,080 --> 01:04:55,200
Right?

958
01:04:56,360 --> 01:04:57,360
Right, love?

959
01:04:57,960 --> 01:04:59,040
Yes, love.

960
01:05:00,000 --> 01:05:01,160
That’s life.

961
01:05:02,480 --> 01:05:04,000
Some build homes,

962
01:05:04,120 --> 01:05:05,240
while others destroy them.

963
01:05:06,840 --> 01:05:08,840
I like Ateş Bey. He’s a very good man.

964
01:05:11,640 --> 01:05:12,720
Mercan Hanım is too.

965
01:05:15,720 --> 01:05:16,760
God is great.

966
01:05:17,200 --> 01:05:19,320
Maybe one day they’ll be happy too.

967
01:05:20,320 --> 01:05:21,320
Amen.

968
01:05:22,240 --> 01:05:23,240
Zehra

969
01:05:23,800 --> 01:05:24,800
What is it?

970
01:05:24,920 --> 01:05:27,640
Could anything good really
come out of your mouth?

971
01:05:30,480 --> 01:05:33,200
I know goodness as well as I
know badness, dear sister-in-law.

972
01:05:34,280 --> 01:05:36,840
What can I do if you can’t
see my optimistic side?

973
01:05:38,680 --> 01:05:39,680
What?

974
01:05:42,600 --> 01:05:43,600
Optimistic

975
01:05:44,560 --> 01:05:45,720
Optimistic?

976
01:05:46,120 --> 01:05:47,320
Optimistic.

977
01:05:47,920 --> 01:05:50,560
If you didn’t learn that word
today and start marketing it to us,

978
01:05:50,600 --> 01:05:52,040
then I know nothing.

979
01:05:52,880 --> 01:05:53,880
Optis..

980
01:05:54,080 --> 01:05:55,720
No, optimistic, love.

981
01:05:56,840 --> 01:05:57,840
Optimistic.

982
01:05:58,400 --> 01:05:59,400
What is that?

983
01:05:59,960 --> 01:06:02,800
You know, thinking good for everything.

984
01:06:02,960 --> 01:06:05,600
Seeing everything good.

985
01:06:05,640 --> 01:06:06,680
Stop all this chatter

986
01:06:07,000 --> 01:06:08,080
Yeah, whatever.

987
01:06:08,240 --> 01:06:09,800
Stop it.

988
01:06:09,960 --> 01:06:11,200
Go to bed.

989
01:06:11,440 --> 01:06:13,720
Come on, everyone to
your rooms, to your nests,

990
01:06:13,960 --> 01:06:15,760
go on.

991
01:06:20,080 --> 01:06:21,640
Tomorrow there’s a world of work to do.

992
01:06:22,400 --> 01:06:23,400
Mother Binnaz

993
01:06:23,480 --> 01:06:25,480
I think you shouldn’t
tire yourselves out so much.

994
01:06:28,160 --> 01:06:29,480
How can that be?

995
01:06:29,880 --> 01:06:33,000
F we’re not going to tire ourselves
out on a day like this, then when will we?

996
01:06:34,240 --> 01:06:35,240
Thank you.

997
01:06:35,880 --> 01:06:36,600
Well,

998
01:06:36,800 --> 01:06:38,999
Marriage is a serious institution, Malik

999
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:41,040
Every step leading up to it matters.

1000
01:06:43,760 --> 01:06:45,800
Yes, sure.

1001
01:06:47,000 --> 01:06:50,240
Serious, yes, but beautiful too.

1002
01:06:52,920 --> 01:06:54,360
For example

1003
01:06:54,840 --> 01:06:56,080
we’re married,

1004
01:06:57,680 --> 01:06:59,240
we’re married,

1005
01:07:01,480 --> 01:07:03,960
and very happy.

1006
01:07:06,000 --> 01:07:08,200
The only thing missing

1007
01:07:10,800 --> 01:07:11,800
is a child.

1008
01:07:20,600 --> 01:07:21,960
God willing,

1009
01:07:22,160 --> 01:07:23,160
God willing

1010
01:07:48,120 --> 01:07:49,360
There’s something on your mind.

1011
01:07:53,960 --> 01:07:54,960
Come on, say it.

1012
01:07:55,360 --> 01:07:56,880
We haven’t been able to talk properly.

1013
01:08:03,920 --> 01:08:05,680
Everything happening around us

1014
01:08:07,200 --> 01:08:08,560
is poisoning our relationship.

1015
01:08:13,200 --> 01:08:14,720
And unfortunately, it doesn’t end.

1016
01:08:15,800 --> 01:08:16,920
And it seems

1017
01:08:17,400 --> 01:08:18,960
it never will.

1018
01:08:22,760 --> 01:08:23,840
What are you trying to say?

1019
01:08:29,600 --> 01:08:31,400
The issue of divorce has been on my mind.

1020
01:08:41,120 --> 01:08:44,240
In the middle of all this evil, I keep
wondering whether our love can survive.

1021
01:08:48,080 --> 01:08:50,480
What happened today made me see the truth.

1022
01:08:53,560 --> 01:08:55,280
What Aslı did affected you

1023
01:08:56,680 --> 01:08:58,600
It’s not just about what she did.

1024
01:09:01,280 --> 01:09:02,920
Everything starts with my father.

1025
01:09:04,880 --> 01:09:07,000
Can we really ignore what he has done?

1026
01:09:08,600 --> 01:09:10,440
Shouldn’t we have moved
past all this by now?

1027
01:09:11,120 --> 01:09:13,480
This madness between the two
families will never end, Ateş.

1028
01:09:15,160 --> 01:09:17,120
This anger, this hatred it will never end.

1029
01:09:23,160 --> 01:09:25,080
Our love will live forever.

1030
01:09:30,120 --> 01:09:31,800
But we are surrounded by evil.

1031
01:09:33,360 --> 01:09:34,360
And on top of that,

1032
01:09:35,480 --> 01:09:38,520
the shadow of everything that happened
in the past will always hang over us.

1033
01:09:44,480 --> 01:09:45,560
It has to end

1034
01:10:01,320 --> 01:10:02,400
sometimes love

1035
01:10:03,240 --> 01:10:05,200
isn’t strong enough
for everything after all

1036
01:10:16,360 --> 01:10:17,360
Let’s get divorced.

1037
01:10:46,640 --> 01:10:49,400
You’ve already been paying for
other people’s crimes for so long.

1038
01:10:54,400 --> 01:10:55,920
If anyone deserves happiness, it’s you

1039
01:11:05,240 --> 01:11:06,800
You are very precious to me, Mercan.

1040
01:11:13,960 --> 01:11:16,320
If our love won’t make you happy,

1041
01:11:24,080 --> 01:11:25,800
I’m even willing to give it up.

1042
01:11:40,960 --> 01:11:43,600
But don’t expect me to
tear it out of my heart.

1043
01:13:22,960 --> 01:13:24,000
Damn it!

1044
01:13:25,240 --> 01:13:27,280
Look at me! Because of her…

1045
01:13:28,520 --> 01:13:30,240
Look at this!

1046
01:13:32,680 --> 01:13:34,120
Look at me!

1047
01:13:36,720 --> 01:13:37,720
Enough,

1048
01:13:40,040 --> 01:13:41,520
you’re making my head spin. Sit down!

1049
01:13:42,440 --> 01:13:43,960
Why should I care about your head!

1050
01:13:44,360 --> 01:13:46,200
If you’re that bothered,
then close your eyes!

1051
01:13:46,800 --> 01:13:49,080
Listen here, crazy woman, shut your mouth

1052
01:13:49,280 --> 01:13:50,840
before I lose my temper!

1053
01:13:51,520 --> 01:13:52,880
And what happens if you do, huh?

1054
01:13:53,440 --> 01:13:54,240
What are you gonna do?

1055
01:13:54,440 --> 01:13:56,200
Come here and see what I’ll do.

1056
01:13:56,720 --> 01:13:57,720
Don’t you dare!

1057
01:13:57,800 --> 01:14:00,000
Don’t even think about
laying those filthy hands on me!

1058
01:14:00,040 --> 01:14:01,040
Let go!
Look at me!

1059
01:14:01,320 --> 01:14:02,880
You’re new here.

1060
01:14:03,240 --> 01:14:05,080
Looks like you need a
little welcome lesson!

1061
01:14:05,400 --> 01:14:06,560
Let go of me!

1062
01:14:07,040 --> 01:14:08,360
Help me!

1063
01:14:09,760 --> 01:14:10,840
Shut up!

1064
01:14:11,560 --> 01:14:12,840
Help me!

1065
01:14:13,640 --> 01:14:14,776
Who do you think you are, girl!

1066
01:14:14,800 --> 01:14:16,119
Who do you think you are

1067
01:14:16,120 --> 01:14:17,200
Who the hell are you?

1068
01:14:17,280 --> 01:14:18,719
Who do you think you are, girl!

1069
01:14:18,720 --> 01:14:19,960
Who are you?

1070
01:14:27,240 --> 01:14:28,480
This isn’t a palace…

1071
01:14:28,640 --> 01:14:31,520
Princesses don’t rule here!

1072
01:14:43,640 --> 01:14:44,680
Oh,

1073
01:14:45,480 --> 01:14:46,480
Zehra.

1074
01:14:46,800 --> 01:14:48,240
This room really worked out well.

1075
01:14:52,640 --> 01:14:54,920
Thanks to my brother Malik.

1076
01:14:56,600 --> 01:14:57,760
You nkow what,

1077
01:14:58,360 --> 01:14:59,840
He’s a good guy, Malik…

1078
01:15:02,400 --> 01:15:04,160
I hope he and Çiçek will be happy.

1079
01:15:05,080 --> 01:15:09,600
Çiçek is all chirpy now, and
she was exactly the same as a kid.

1080
01:15:10,360 --> 01:15:12,920
Honestly, wish you’d seen her.

1081
01:15:23,480 --> 01:15:24,480
Zehra

1082
01:15:28,520 --> 01:15:30,120
Wouldn’t it be nice if we had a daughter

1083
01:15:30,680 --> 01:15:32,560
and she looked like you?

1084
01:15:34,440 --> 01:15:36,760
I’m thinking about our family’s future.

1085
01:15:36,800 --> 01:15:37,880
I’m really hopeful.

1086
01:15:38,040 --> 01:15:39,040
Zehra I'm happy.

1087
01:15:40,200 --> 01:15:41,640
I think we’re going to be very happy

1088
01:15:42,880 --> 01:15:43,520
Berat,

1089
01:15:43,560 --> 01:15:45,800
why did you bring up the kid
thing in front of everyone?

1090
01:15:46,560 --> 01:15:47,560
Shouldn’t I have?

1091
01:15:47,960 --> 01:15:50,920
We hadn’t even talked about it
ourselves, so why are you telling them?

1092
01:15:51,880 --> 01:15:53,160
That’s not okay, Berat.

1093
01:15:53,840 --> 01:15:56,200
What’s the problem, Zehra?
What happens if I say it?

1094
01:15:56,600 --> 01:15:58,440
Don’t say it, Berat! Don’t say it.

1095
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:02,440
You tell everyone things
that concern only us.

1096
01:16:05,600 --> 01:16:06,880
Are they just everyone, my love?

1097
01:16:08,320 --> 01:16:10,080
Look, these four walls…

1098
01:16:10,880 --> 01:16:13,680
Some things should stay
within these four walls.

1099
01:16:15,880 --> 01:16:17,040
Go away.

1100
01:16:18,720 --> 01:16:19,720
Go away!

1101
01:16:22,560 --> 01:16:23,560
Good night.

1102
01:16:29,120 --> 01:16:30,120
Good night.

1103
01:17:06,320 --> 01:17:08,720
You’re slipping through my
fingers right before my eyes,

1104
01:17:08,960 --> 01:17:10,360
and there’s nothing I can do.

1105
01:17:21,880 --> 01:17:22,880
Don’t go…

1106
01:17:47,560 --> 01:17:50,200
Tell me something beautiful…

1107
01:17:56,880 --> 01:17:58,520
I once heard it from someone named Tahir.

1108
01:18:00,240 --> 01:18:01,360
Tahir, huh?

1109
01:18:02,920 --> 01:18:04,240
Sounds familiar.

1110
01:18:05,960 --> 01:18:07,560
Of course it does.

1111
01:18:11,320 --> 01:18:13,720
This Tahir of ours had fallen
in love with a beautiful girl.

1112
01:18:15,200 --> 01:18:17,240
He had known her since childhood too.

1113
01:18:19,280 --> 01:18:20,280
Hmm, really?

1114
01:18:21,440 --> 01:18:22,960
And what was this girl’s name?

1115
01:18:24,920 --> 01:18:25,920
İnci Mercan.

1116
01:18:30,800 --> 01:18:32,200
That sounds very familiar too.

1117
01:18:33,440 --> 01:18:34,600
I wonder who she is.

1118
01:18:36,960 --> 01:18:38,160
I’ve seen her before.

1119
01:18:40,280 --> 01:18:41,480
She’s very beautiful.

1120
01:18:45,480 --> 01:18:46,480
Very beautiful.

1121
01:18:53,560 --> 01:18:55,600
But you’re making me forget the fairy tale.

1122
01:18:56,560 --> 01:18:58,240
I’m quiet, okay.

1123
01:19:01,720 --> 01:19:02,720
What was I saying…

1124
01:19:02,920 --> 01:19:03,920
Right.

1125
01:19:04,040 --> 01:19:06,280
This Tahir was in love
with a beautiful girl.

1126
01:19:08,800 --> 01:19:10,080
With the color of her eyes,

1127
01:19:15,680 --> 01:19:16,880
her hair

1128
01:19:22,160 --> 01:19:23,800
the softness of her skin,

1129
01:19:29,760 --> 01:19:32,400
that tiny line that appeared on
her forehead when she got angry...

1130
01:19:32,480 --> 01:19:33,800
the dimple in her chin...

1131
01:19:36,080 --> 01:19:38,280
He was separately smitten
with every single part of her

1132
01:19:42,480 --> 01:19:44,560
That’s why his love never ended.

1133
01:19:46,520 --> 01:19:48,160
Their love grew so great

1134
01:19:49,880 --> 01:19:51,400
that all seven realms heard of it.

1135
01:19:56,280 --> 01:19:58,720
Even the sun became jealous of them.

1136
01:20:01,400 --> 01:20:03,120
The sun asked Tahir for his love

1137
01:20:05,640 --> 01:20:08,120
If he didn’t give up his love,
the sun would never rise again.

1138
01:20:10,240 --> 01:20:11,520
Tahir thought it over.

1139
01:20:13,920 --> 01:20:15,720
If he gave up his love,

1140
01:20:17,440 --> 01:20:18,880
if he gave up his pearl Mercan,

1141
01:20:20,160 --> 01:20:21,840
his life would already be dark.

1142
01:20:26,360 --> 01:20:27,880
So let the sun not rise then.

1143
01:20:28,160 --> 01:20:29,520
He did not give up his love.

1144
01:20:30,480 --> 01:20:31,920
The sun got angry at this

1145
01:20:32,680 --> 01:20:33,880
and did not rise the next day.

1146
01:20:39,840 --> 01:20:41,520
But Tahir and İnci Mercan’s love

1147
01:20:41,760 --> 01:20:43,640
was so great

1148
01:20:48,080 --> 01:20:50,040
that they became fire and lit up the night.

1149
01:21:01,600 --> 01:21:02,640
Good night.

1150
01:21:04,040 --> 01:21:05,160
Good night,

1151
01:21:58,920 --> 01:22:01,280
Every minute brings
us closer to separation.

1152
01:22:02,200 --> 01:22:03,920
If only I could stop time…

1153
01:22:16,880 --> 01:22:19,320
This is the last morning
I wake up and see you.

1154
01:22:20,080 --> 01:22:21,680
How will I endure it…

1155
01:22:21,920 --> 01:22:23,920
How will I manage to live without you..?

1156
01:22:26,720 --> 01:22:27,720
Good morning…

1157
01:22:28,720 --> 01:22:29,720
Good morning.

1158
01:22:34,160 --> 01:22:36,040
Big day today, are you ready?

1159
01:22:38,760 --> 01:22:39,760
What,

1160
01:22:40,640 --> 01:22:42,360
can’t wait to get divorced?

1161
01:22:44,280 --> 01:22:46,480
I didn’t mean the divorce.

1162
01:22:47,480 --> 01:22:49,720
I meant we’re going to ask
for Malik’s hand in marriage.

1163
01:22:50,800 --> 01:22:51,800
That..

1164
01:22:53,040 --> 01:22:55,120
I can’t think about anything else.

1165
01:22:55,480 --> 01:22:56,720
I misunderstood

1166
01:23:01,000 --> 01:23:02,000
Right,

1167
01:23:02,520 --> 01:23:03,520
Life...

1168
01:23:06,000 --> 01:23:07,320
On one hand, a sad ending,

1169
01:23:09,640 --> 01:23:11,400
on the other, a beginning
full of happiness…

1170
01:23:13,600 --> 01:23:14,960
If only a miracle happened…

1171
01:23:15,600 --> 01:23:16,840
If only I could run to you.

1172
01:23:19,520 --> 01:23:20,960
If only a miracle happened…

1173
01:23:22,640 --> 01:23:23,640
If only you were mine.

1174
01:23:29,240 --> 01:23:30,760
Come on, get up.

1175
01:23:31,080 --> 01:23:32,360
It was nice like this.

1176
01:23:33,120 --> 01:23:34,880
If you’re going to
use the bathroom, go now,

1177
01:23:35,040 --> 01:23:37,321
because once I go in, I never
come out, just so you know.

1178
01:23:50,160 --> 01:23:51,760
I'll go first.

1179
01:24:25,880 --> 01:24:26,880
You cheated.

1180
01:24:28,760 --> 01:24:29,840
It wasn’t cheating.

1181
01:24:32,040 --> 01:24:33,040
But it worked.

1182
01:24:35,760 --> 01:24:37,680
So you’re saying you
didn’t do it to cheat, huh?

1183
01:24:57,640 --> 01:24:59,200
Mother, you're awake!

1184
01:25:01,200 --> 01:25:03,520
Today’s the big day, get up

1185
01:25:03,840 --> 01:25:05,440
Oh, you're excited!

1186
01:25:12,120 --> 01:25:13,720
Why are you distracted?

1187
01:25:14,840 --> 01:25:16,920
My mind was on Berat, I couldn’t sleep…

1188
01:25:18,160 --> 01:25:19,160
Why?

1189
01:25:19,320 --> 01:25:20,720
That child thing he mentioned…

1190
01:25:21,320 --> 01:25:23,640
Oh yes, right, shocking, huh.

1191
01:25:24,880 --> 01:25:26,320
It’s a shock to us now,

1192
01:25:26,520 --> 01:25:28,960
tomorrow it’ll be a shock to him too.

1193
01:25:29,800 --> 01:25:31,880
Berat is still a child himself.

1194
01:25:32,200 --> 01:25:36,360
His head’s in the clouds.
He thinks it’s easy…

1195
01:25:38,960 --> 01:25:42,080
Making one is easy, but raising one isn’t…

1196
01:25:43,960 --> 01:25:46,040
And they only just got married too!

1197
01:25:46,480 --> 01:25:48,480
Suppose they can’t get along, then what?

1198
01:25:48,840 --> 01:25:51,440
And with a child hanging
from their skirts too…

1199
01:25:55,160 --> 01:25:56,160
I mean,

1200
01:25:56,680 --> 01:25:58,040
I get it, you’re right…

1201
01:25:58,640 --> 01:26:01,720
It’s the first time I’ve
seen my brother this excited.

1202
01:26:02,200 --> 01:26:04,040
His eyes were literally shining.

1203
01:26:05,320 --> 01:26:06,320
What is it?

1204
01:26:06,440 --> 01:26:08,760
Weren't you against them?

1205
01:26:10,480 --> 01:26:12,000
Maybe I'm wrong.

1206
01:26:15,520 --> 01:26:17,680
Doesn’t a person have
to take responsibility

1207
01:26:17,800 --> 01:26:20,400
and face hardship in
order to grow spiritually?

1208
01:26:22,000 --> 01:26:24,200
Maybe that’s what would mature Berat.

1209
01:26:26,120 --> 01:26:27,120
Yeah.

1210
01:26:27,280 --> 01:26:28,280
Right.

1211
01:26:28,440 --> 01:26:32,440
What wouldn’t I give for a
grandchild running around this house.

1212
01:26:32,920 --> 01:26:34,520
I would want it.

1213
01:26:34,720 --> 01:26:35,960
I told you,

1214
01:26:36,160 --> 01:26:37,840
I don’t trust it, daughter

1215
01:26:38,040 --> 01:26:40,080
I mean, you know Zehra.

1216
01:26:40,200 --> 01:26:42,560
And ours is a different
story, he acts smart on a whim…

1217
01:26:43,200 --> 01:26:44,840
How will this ever happen?

1218
01:26:45,680 --> 01:26:47,600
Oh my Berat.

1219
01:26:47,840 --> 01:26:49,240
My naive son.

1220
01:26:49,600 --> 01:26:51,560
My Berat always acts from here.

1221
01:26:52,040 --> 01:26:54,200
But to be a mother and father,

1222
01:26:54,240 --> 01:26:55,960
you need to use this too

1223
01:27:00,480 --> 01:27:02,999
Who knows, maybe our child
will come before theirs.

1224
01:27:03,000 --> 01:27:04,000
Mom.

1225
01:27:04,160 --> 01:27:05,640
What are you saying!

1226
01:27:05,680 --> 01:27:06,400
Mom!

1227
01:27:06,520 --> 01:27:09,080
I'll go, I was joking!

1228
01:27:09,240 --> 01:27:10,240
Okay!

1229
01:27:10,760 --> 01:27:13,080
You naughty, Çiçek!

1230
01:27:16,880 --> 01:27:18,280
Oh my Berat!

1231
01:27:19,560 --> 01:27:21,640
It's not a bad idea, actually.

1232
01:27:22,560 --> 01:27:24,640
How will take care of it?

1233
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:30,080
Oh Lord.

1234
01:27:43,040 --> 01:27:44,040
Aslı!

1235
01:27:48,360 --> 01:27:49,360
Mom!

1236
01:27:50,800 --> 01:27:51,800
My girl

1237
01:27:57,360 --> 01:27:59,480
Aslı!? My girl, what happened to you?!

1238
01:28:02,120 --> 01:28:03,960
Who did this?

1239
01:28:05,640 --> 01:28:07,520
Ah, I got into a fight with some lunatic.

1240
01:28:09,440 --> 01:28:10,440
You’re okay, right?

1241
01:28:10,640 --> 01:28:12,400
Oh my God! Nothing serious, right?

1242
01:28:12,880 --> 01:28:15,120
How can I be okay in here, Mom!

1243
01:28:15,600 --> 01:28:17,040
Look at this!

1244
01:28:18,920 --> 01:28:20,840
What am I even doing here…

1245
01:28:21,000 --> 01:28:22,840
Like a criminal!

1246
01:28:24,720 --> 01:28:26,360
Mom, do something…

1247
01:28:26,840 --> 01:28:28,200
Get me out of here.

1248
01:28:29,960 --> 01:28:31,240
Oh, Aslı! Oh!

1249
01:28:32,320 --> 01:28:34,360
I told you, daughter.

1250
01:28:35,280 --> 01:28:37,600
You never listened! It was
obvious we’d end up in trouble…

1251
01:28:38,440 --> 01:28:41,160
This is what happens when
you act without thinking!

1252
01:28:41,600 --> 01:28:42,600
Mom,

1253
01:28:43,160 --> 01:28:45,880
do I look like I’m in the mood
to listen to a lecture right now!

1254
01:28:48,880 --> 01:28:51,400
If Ateş gives them that
video, I’m finished.

1255
01:28:52,960 --> 01:28:54,880
Do something!

1256
01:28:55,320 --> 01:28:56,920
Get me out of here, Mom.

1257
01:28:56,960 --> 01:28:58,520
I can’t stay here… I’ll die!

1258
01:28:59,200 --> 01:29:01,480
Okay, okay, calm down.

1259
01:29:02,240 --> 01:29:04,440
I’ll get you out…

1260
01:29:06,640 --> 01:29:08,160
But be careful.

1261
01:29:08,440 --> 01:29:10,280
Stay away from that crazy woman too.

1262
01:29:10,680 --> 01:29:11,680
Okay

1263
01:29:13,920 --> 01:29:15,560
I’ll do what I can.

1264
01:29:25,040 --> 01:29:26,800
Be careful.

1265
01:29:27,600 --> 01:29:29,240
I left some clean clothes.

1266
01:29:32,600 --> 01:29:33,920
Take care.

1267
01:29:34,440 --> 01:29:35,440
See you.

1268
01:30:06,880 --> 01:30:07,920
Oh mother,

1269
01:30:12,880 --> 01:30:14,720
I’m seriously sore.

1270
01:30:15,680 --> 01:30:17,640
My back, neck..

1271
01:30:21,960 --> 01:30:22,960
Love,

1272
01:30:23,840 --> 01:30:25,800
You should maasage me later.

1273
01:30:26,280 --> 01:30:27,720
I’m seriously sore.

1274
01:30:33,200 --> 01:30:34,200
Zehra,

1275
01:30:34,720 --> 01:30:36,040
you won’t even look at my face,

1276
01:30:36,520 --> 01:30:37,880
I’m busy, Berat.

1277
01:30:41,240 --> 01:30:42,240
Love,

1278
01:30:47,360 --> 01:30:48,360
Dear,

1279
01:30:48,920 --> 01:30:51,920
Don’t you even have time
to greet your husband, girl?

1280
01:30:53,200 --> 01:30:54,680
I don’t want a child, Berat.

1281
01:30:57,760 --> 01:31:00,760
Don’t go around talking like you’ve
got “child, child” stuck to your mouth.

1282
01:31:07,040 --> 01:31:08,040
Calm down.

1283
01:31:08,960 --> 01:31:10,280
What's this reaction?

1284
01:31:13,240 --> 01:31:14,400
It never even

1285
01:31:14,680 --> 01:31:17,240
occurred to me that you might not want one…

1286
01:31:20,080 --> 01:31:23,440
Children give energy, love...

1287
01:31:23,840 --> 01:31:25,200
I mean, who doesn’t love children…

1288
01:31:29,240 --> 01:31:30,840
It’s not that I don’t love them…

1289
01:31:34,160 --> 01:31:36,080
I’m just not ready yet.

1290
01:31:38,280 --> 01:31:39,960
I grew up on my own.

1291
01:31:41,280 --> 01:31:42,280
Myself.

1292
01:31:43,080 --> 01:31:44,760
I never saw what motherhood was.

1293
01:31:49,560 --> 01:31:51,400
I don’t know how it’s done, that’s why.

1294
01:31:53,920 --> 01:31:54,920
I mean..

1295
01:31:55,160 --> 01:31:57,400
Let it happen when I feel ready,

1296
01:31:59,400 --> 01:32:02,360
so I can do whatever
is necessary as a mother.

1297
01:32:05,640 --> 01:32:07,080
Protect them,

1298
01:32:08,200 --> 01:32:10,480
care for them, feed them…

1299
01:32:21,760 --> 01:32:22,760
You’re right,

1300
01:32:23,000 --> 01:32:24,840
You’re right, my wife.
I didn’t think of that,

1301
01:32:25,520 --> 01:32:26,520
forgive me

1302
01:32:28,400 --> 01:32:29,400
Me as usual.

1303
01:32:32,400 --> 01:32:33,520
As long as you’re happy,

1304
01:32:34,280 --> 01:32:35,320
you smile,

1305
01:32:38,760 --> 01:32:40,240
let it be however you want.

1306
01:32:42,440 --> 01:32:43,440
Calm down.

1307
01:32:43,600 --> 01:32:44,600
Come here.

1308
01:32:55,600 --> 01:32:56,680
Aw, I can’t bear it for you

1309
01:32:57,880 --> 01:32:59,000
Calm.

1310
01:33:00,160 --> 01:33:02,080
Don’t be upset.

1311
01:33:03,080 --> 01:33:04,600
What’s the big deal.

1312
01:33:05,720 --> 01:33:06,720
My bella.

1313
01:33:10,560 --> 01:33:11,920
We’ll do it next month.

1314
01:33:11,960 --> 01:33:12,960
What’s the big deal.
What?

1315
01:33:14,680 --> 01:33:16,080
I’m saying we can do it next month

1316
01:33:16,640 --> 01:33:17,799
You’ll be ready in a month, probably.

1317
01:33:17,800 --> 01:33:18,800
Berat!

1318
01:33:22,840 --> 01:33:23,840
No, you won’t…

1319
01:33:25,680 --> 01:33:26,840
I can’t either, anyway…

1320
01:33:27,720 --> 01:33:28,720
I can’t

1321
01:33:30,240 --> 01:33:31,240
Two months.

1322
01:33:33,760 --> 01:33:35,360
We'll talk about it.

1323
01:33:35,720 --> 01:33:36,720
We will.

1324
01:33:36,880 --> 01:33:37,880
We'll talk.

1325
01:33:38,400 --> 01:33:39,400
Then..

1326
01:33:41,400 --> 01:33:42,400
Smile.

1327
01:34:29,800 --> 01:34:31,000
You look very beautiful

1328
01:34:33,640 --> 01:34:36,440
I thought I’d get ready early
for Çiçek’s asking ceremony.

1329
01:34:42,160 --> 01:34:44,680
Why did you have breakfast set up out here?

1330
01:34:47,840 --> 01:34:49,960
I wanted our last breakfast
to be just the two of us.

1331
01:34:51,120 --> 01:34:52,800
But if you want, we can go inside.

1332
01:34:53,480 --> 01:34:55,440
No, you thought of it very well.

1333
01:35:01,040 --> 01:35:02,040
Thanks.

1334
01:35:14,640 --> 01:35:16,040
I had the pastry made for you.

1335
01:35:16,800 --> 01:35:19,560
That one time, you almost
ate all of them on the table…

1336
01:35:24,160 --> 01:35:25,160
You remember…

1337
01:35:27,800 --> 01:35:29,600
I don’t forget anything about you.

1338
01:35:32,240 --> 01:35:33,240
And I never will…

1339
01:35:37,280 --> 01:35:38,280
And the olives

1340
01:35:38,400 --> 01:35:39,520
were specially brought

1341
01:35:39,680 --> 01:35:41,320
from Gemlik for Miss Mercan.

1342
01:35:43,720 --> 01:35:44,960
That was too much trouble.

1343
01:35:46,040 --> 01:35:47,080
Yes. It was a bit.

1344
01:35:47,960 --> 01:35:48,960
I put in a lot of effort.

1345
01:35:50,200 --> 01:35:52,320
But no matter how much I
do, it’s too little for you…

1346
01:35:56,000 --> 01:35:57,639
I should have done something too, at least.

1347
01:35:57,640 --> 01:35:58,640
No, you shouldn’t.

1348
01:35:59,920 --> 01:36:01,040
Oh, come on.

1349
01:36:04,640 --> 01:36:05,720
Let there always be love.

1350
01:36:33,800 --> 01:36:36,000
Well, of course, when
you’re not used to it…

1351
01:36:36,200 --> 01:36:37,440
Come here.

1352
01:36:44,880 --> 01:36:46,200
I put it here,

1353
01:36:46,520 --> 01:36:48,080
This is there,

1354
01:36:51,760 --> 01:36:53,320
Desserts are ready.

1355
01:36:53,720 --> 01:36:57,960
This is too salty, I
should've made them again.

1356
01:36:58,040 --> 01:36:59,360
Mother.

1357
01:37:00,840 --> 01:37:03,880
Mom, slow down, for heaven’s
sake. They are all delicious.

1358
01:37:04,320 --> 01:37:05,320
Yeah.

1359
01:37:05,600 --> 01:37:07,280
Okay, great.

1360
01:37:09,880 --> 01:37:10,880
Berat

1361
01:37:11,640 --> 01:37:13,560
Good thing we got married in secret.

1362
01:37:14,200 --> 01:37:16,360
Look at her, she can’t
stay in place from excitement,

1363
01:37:16,760 --> 01:37:17,960
Yeah, seriously.

1364
01:37:18,200 --> 01:37:19,800
Something’s going to happen, God forbid.

1365
01:37:20,880 --> 01:37:24,280
Not a bride’s house, a disaster zone…

1366
01:37:24,600 --> 01:37:25,600
seriously

1367
01:37:27,880 --> 01:37:29,800
We're running late.

1368
01:37:31,600 --> 01:37:32,600
Mom,

1369
01:37:33,040 --> 01:37:34,480
slow down,

1370
01:37:34,840 --> 01:37:37,120
Son, we're running late!

1371
01:37:38,440 --> 01:37:40,080
If you carry on like this,

1372
01:37:40,400 --> 01:37:41,936
before you even get to see
your daughter’s big day,

1373
01:37:41,960 --> 01:37:42,960
God forbid

1374
01:38:11,880 --> 01:38:15,160
Mashallah!

1375
01:38:34,200 --> 01:38:37,880
May God always keep your face
smiling like this. My angel girl…

1376
01:38:40,240 --> 01:38:41,480
is this our tiny Çiçek?

1377
01:38:44,800 --> 01:38:46,880
You look beautiful

1378
01:38:48,120 --> 01:38:51,080
There’s a princess
standing in front of me, Mom

1379
01:38:51,920 --> 01:38:52,920
Mashallajh

1380
01:38:54,080 --> 01:38:55,160
Masallah

1381
01:38:56,240 --> 01:38:57,600
My little sister

1382
01:38:58,360 --> 01:38:59,680
has really grown up, huh.

1383
01:39:06,960 --> 01:39:08,560
Is this our tiny Çiçek?

1384
01:39:09,360 --> 01:39:13,360
Stop, you’re going to make me
cry too… My makeup will get ruined.

1385
01:39:13,480 --> 01:39:14,480
Mom.

1386
01:39:15,640 --> 01:39:16,640
It passed.

1387
01:39:18,000 --> 01:39:19,000
Okay.

1388
01:39:26,240 --> 01:39:28,720
There is way too much love
in this room… Way too much!

1389
01:39:29,000 --> 01:39:30,000
It’s overwhelming me!

1390
01:39:33,240 --> 01:39:34,240
Love, it's..

1391
01:39:34,440 --> 01:39:36,560
My love for you.

1392
01:39:38,440 --> 01:39:39,920
It's way too much for the house.

1393
01:39:53,440 --> 01:39:54,840
After court,

1394
01:39:57,400 --> 01:39:59,240
will you come back home?

1395
01:40:00,600 --> 01:40:01,840
Or will you go abroad directly?

1396
01:40:03,480 --> 01:40:04,760
I haven’t thought about it yet…

1397
01:40:06,360 --> 01:40:07,720
And I don’t want to.

1398
01:40:08,720 --> 01:40:10,040
Right now

1399
01:40:10,280 --> 01:40:12,600
I want to focus on asking for Malik’s hand.

1400
01:40:13,640 --> 01:40:17,040
They give me hope that
beautiful things still exist.

1401
01:40:17,400 --> 01:40:18,840
So our separation is unimportant?

1402
01:40:19,560 --> 01:40:21,760
Not even worth thinking about…

1403
01:40:24,000 --> 01:40:25,000
Exactly.

1404
01:40:25,720 --> 01:40:27,160
You understood perfectly, as always.

1405
01:40:29,040 --> 01:40:30,040
Mercan!

1406
01:40:30,320 --> 01:40:31,320
Ateş!

1407
01:40:32,040 --> 01:40:33,040
Go ahead!

1408
01:40:33,320 --> 01:40:34,320
No, you go ahead.

1409
01:40:35,680 --> 01:40:36,680
King of sulking.

1410
01:40:37,240 --> 01:40:38,880
You misunderstood again.

1411
01:40:39,960 --> 01:40:40,960
Fine, fine.

1412
01:40:41,960 --> 01:40:43,920
Let’s always have hope for other people.

1413
01:40:45,760 --> 01:40:47,080
You barely ate anything. Eat.

1414
01:40:47,880 --> 01:40:48,440
Thanks,

1415
01:40:48,760 --> 01:40:49,760
but I have no appetite.

1416
01:40:54,800 --> 01:40:56,160
Same here.

1417
01:40:58,160 --> 01:40:59,600
I’m going to the study.

1418
01:41:00,720 --> 01:41:02,640
There are some files I need to look over.

1419
01:41:04,480 --> 01:41:06,360
Let the hopeless ones work.

1420
01:41:08,920 --> 01:41:10,880
I’ll go upstairs and
get Çiçek’s gift ready.

1421
01:41:12,240 --> 01:41:13,600
Since there’s hope for them.

1422
01:41:13,720 --> 01:41:15,200
Go on, go on.

1423
01:41:20,880 --> 01:41:22,960
You made a mess here.

1424
01:41:24,080 --> 01:41:25,360
Drop this, Nermin.

1425
01:41:25,720 --> 01:41:27,440
It’s finally over. We’re getting rid of it.

1426
01:41:28,400 --> 01:41:30,600
The big moment is today.

1427
01:41:31,400 --> 01:41:33,080
Ateş will both get out of Mercan’s life

1428
01:41:33,120 --> 01:41:35,560
and go to prison and be
kicked out of the company.

1429
01:41:35,760 --> 01:41:37,360
All together.

1430
01:41:39,200 --> 01:41:41,840
If you ask me, we got through the bad days,

1431
01:41:42,360 --> 01:41:44,160
and now the worse days are coming.

1432
01:41:44,800 --> 01:41:47,160
Shut that ominous mouth of yours!

1433
01:41:47,600 --> 01:41:49,080
I’m just saying what is

1434
01:41:52,320 --> 01:41:53,320
My daughter…

1435
01:41:53,840 --> 01:41:55,200
Come, dear Mercan.

1436
01:41:56,280 --> 01:41:57,280
Mercan.

1437
01:41:59,760 --> 01:42:00,760
So?

1438
01:42:00,840 --> 01:42:02,720
Have you thought again
about the alimony issue?

1439
01:42:05,720 --> 01:42:08,320
Look, when you think about it,
you’ll come around to where I

1440
01:42:09,640 --> 01:42:10,960
I’m very clear, Mom.

1441
01:42:11,720 --> 01:42:12,960
There’s nothing to think about…

1442
01:42:13,640 --> 01:42:15,560
I’ve said it before, I don’t want anything.

1443
01:42:16,400 --> 01:42:17,640
The only thing I want is peace.

1444
01:42:18,720 --> 01:42:20,840
And because I know I won’t find that here,

1445
01:42:21,200 --> 01:42:23,400
I’ll go straight back to
Italy after the court hearing.

1446
01:42:24,400 --> 01:42:25,400
Daughter,

1447
01:42:25,920 --> 01:42:27,720
The Karahans will be
the ones leaving anyway.

1448
01:42:28,000 --> 01:42:29,320
Why would you need to go?

1449
01:42:29,960 --> 01:42:30,520
Oh yes,

1450
01:42:30,920 --> 01:42:32,080
exactly,

1451
01:42:32,720 --> 01:42:35,240
how much time is left
on the contract anyway…

1452
01:42:36,560 --> 01:42:37,560
What about you?

1453
01:42:42,280 --> 01:42:44,000
The Karahans are here today, gone tomorrow…

1454
01:42:44,880 --> 01:42:46,640
So they’re not my real concern.

1455
01:42:51,440 --> 01:42:53,640
You are the real reason for my unhappiness.

1456
01:42:54,560 --> 01:42:56,240
I don’t want to live with you.

1457
01:42:58,560 --> 01:43:01,560
Somehow you can survive a blow from others,

1458
01:43:07,440 --> 01:43:09,240
but when it comes from
those closest to you,

1459
01:43:10,200 --> 01:43:11,320
that’s when it destroys you…

1460
01:43:13,640 --> 01:43:15,160
After all the lies, pain,

1461
01:43:15,400 --> 01:43:19,040
I can’t keep up the lie of a
happy family as if nothing happened.

1462
01:43:39,560 --> 01:43:40,920
What’s the status of the shipment?

1463
01:43:41,920 --> 01:43:42,920
Everything is ready.

1464
01:43:43,520 --> 01:43:45,080
The vehicles are about to hit the road.

1465
01:44:35,240 --> 01:44:36,360
Shoot me in the head.

1466
01:44:43,040 --> 01:44:44,960
Yeah, I made a mistake

1467
01:44:47,640 --> 01:44:49,096
just a very short moment, I got confused,

1468
01:44:49,120 --> 01:44:50,519
But I was going to tell you.

1469
01:44:50,520 --> 01:44:52,760
I don't have anyone but you in this life.

1470
01:44:52,960 --> 01:44:53,960
Mother, father..

1471
01:45:01,040 --> 01:45:02,560
Only a brother.

1472
01:45:04,160 --> 01:45:05,360
If you don't believe me

1473
01:45:07,120 --> 01:45:08,120
Shoot me in the head.

1474
01:45:12,720 --> 01:45:15,840
You don't get your hands
blooded, I'll shoot myself.

1475
01:45:21,480 --> 01:45:23,920
Your my brother, how
could I ever wronged you?

1476
01:45:45,960 --> 01:45:47,160
I need to talk

1477
01:45:47,480 --> 01:45:48,480
to both of you.

1478
01:45:55,640 --> 01:45:57,760
When a mother is speaking,
a child does not walk away

1479
01:46:03,120 --> 01:46:04,120
He listens…

1480
01:46:18,320 --> 01:46:19,760
Why did we come here…

1481
01:46:20,360 --> 01:46:21,360
what have we become.

1482
01:46:22,600 --> 01:46:24,680
We were supposed to
tear the Yıldırıms apart,

1483
01:46:26,080 --> 01:46:28,000
and instead we ourselves are shattered

1484
01:46:36,440 --> 01:46:40,440
But the thing that tied us
together was greater than blood

1485
01:46:46,840 --> 01:46:47,920
We have a common purpose

1486
01:46:48,640 --> 01:46:49,800
a common pain

1487
01:46:57,760 --> 01:46:59,520
The Yıldırıms ruined our past,

1488
01:46:59,560 --> 01:47:01,960
and they’re doing the same
to our present, can’t you see!

1489
01:47:02,920 --> 01:47:04,800
We need to become united again.

1490
01:47:05,040 --> 01:47:07,120
That is what befits us and our dead.

1491
01:47:13,960 --> 01:47:15,680
You saw me as a mother,

1492
01:47:16,160 --> 01:47:17,520
and I saw you as my sons.

1493
01:47:26,880 --> 01:47:30,560
My purpose and my duty are
to keep my children together.

1494
01:47:34,960 --> 01:47:36,360
Even if Aslı does evil,

1495
01:47:36,640 --> 01:47:37,719
makes mistakes,

1496
01:47:37,720 --> 01:47:39,519
even if she turns this whole
world upside down for me,

1497
01:47:39,520 --> 01:47:40,520
she is my child.

1498
01:47:41,280 --> 01:47:43,520
A mother’s scale weighs differently…

1499
01:47:44,120 --> 01:47:47,120
If even a pebble touches her nail…
it feels like a boulder sits in my heart

1500
01:47:47,400 --> 01:47:48,760
Just as it would for you.

1501
01:47:54,520 --> 01:47:56,120
The reason Aslı is in this state

1502
01:47:56,480 --> 01:47:58,000
is Haydar Yıldırım.

1503
01:48:04,240 --> 01:48:05,720
Turn back from your decision, son.

1504
01:48:07,680 --> 01:48:09,720
You came here to burn others;

1505
01:48:10,200 --> 01:48:12,400
don’t lose your direction
and turn us to ashes instead…

1506
01:48:52,080 --> 01:48:53,480
What are you doing here!

1507
01:48:53,960 --> 01:48:55,200
I wish you had let me know.

1508
01:48:55,920 --> 01:48:57,159
There are some family issues.

1509
01:48:57,160 --> 01:48:58,280
My hands are very full.

1510
01:48:58,840 --> 01:49:01,040
I called you many times
and couldn’t reach you.

1511
01:49:01,320 --> 01:49:06,000
I found the mansion from the
newspapers with all those big headlines

1512
01:49:14,640 --> 01:49:16,160
You did well, but…
now is not the time.

1513
01:49:16,720 --> 01:49:17,720
I’ll call you,

1514
01:49:17,960 --> 01:49:19,120
don’t worry.

1515
01:49:19,800 --> 01:49:20,960
I needed money.

1516
01:49:21,200 --> 01:49:22,680
I didn’t come out of pleasure either.

1517
01:49:23,080 --> 01:49:23,560
All right.

1518
01:49:23,720 --> 01:49:25,000
I’ll arrange the money.

1519
01:49:25,600 --> 01:49:26,600
Go now.
I’ll call you.

1520
01:49:33,080 --> 01:49:34,080
Müzeyyen mother…

1521
01:49:39,880 --> 01:49:40,880
Ateş

1522
01:49:49,680 --> 01:49:51,520
I’m ready, let’s go.

1523
01:49:52,560 --> 01:49:54,760
They say you shouldn’t keep
a blessed occasion waiting.

1524
01:50:31,720 --> 01:50:34,160
Did you at least prepare your
speech for the asking ceremony?

1525
01:50:34,600 --> 01:50:35,600
No.

1526
01:50:35,880 --> 01:50:37,120
You’ll feed me the lines.

1527
01:50:37,840 --> 01:50:39,840
I didn’t prepare notes
and I’m not giving you any.

1528
01:50:41,040 --> 01:50:42,200
You hardworking student, you.

1529
01:50:42,560 --> 01:50:43,680
That I am.

1530
01:50:44,880 --> 01:50:47,600
Do you remember the advice Güllü
sister and Durmuş brother gave us?

1531
01:50:48,320 --> 01:50:49,320
Yes,

1532
01:50:49,960 --> 01:50:52,360
Durmuş brother told you not
to go against your wife’s word,

1533
01:50:52,480 --> 01:50:55,040
only then would you be happy.

1534
01:50:56,240 --> 01:50:58,000
I see that’s the first
thing you remembered.

1535
01:50:59,680 --> 01:51:01,600
I thought it was very true.

1536
01:51:01,960 --> 01:51:04,040
All men should listen…

1537
01:51:04,440 --> 01:51:06,080
It stayed in my mind…

1538
01:51:06,720 --> 01:51:08,520
What stayed in my mind was

1539
01:51:08,800 --> 01:51:11,216
those crooked little gözleme
pastries you made with Gülsüm sister.

1540
01:51:11,240 --> 01:51:12,240
Crooked?

1541
01:51:12,840 --> 01:51:14,320
Let’s not say crooked,

1542
01:51:14,440 --> 01:51:15,960
let’s say experimental forms.

1543
01:51:16,640 --> 01:51:19,040
You were slurping them
down happily enough though

1544
01:51:20,920 --> 01:51:22,280
Because they came from your hands.

1545
01:51:26,200 --> 01:51:27,200
Their house was

1546
01:51:28,080 --> 01:51:31,960
the only place where we could spend
time without war and hatred around us.

1547
01:51:37,760 --> 01:51:38,880
We were happy there…

1548
01:51:45,400 --> 01:51:47,960
When I was a child… I
decided to jump off this bridge.

1549
01:51:50,720 --> 01:51:51,960
Childish thinking, I guess…

1550
01:51:53,360 --> 01:51:54,880
Tahir stopped me,

1551
01:51:55,400 --> 01:51:56,720
saved me…

1552
01:51:58,960 --> 01:51:59,960
I know Tahir.

1553
01:52:00,840 --> 01:52:01,840
He’s a good boy.

1554
01:52:02,920 --> 01:52:04,920
He is, he is. I love him too.

1555
01:52:07,680 --> 01:52:08,680
That much?

1556
01:52:09,320 --> 01:52:10,320
Very much.

1557
01:52:12,360 --> 01:52:13,720
Should I be jealous?

1558
01:52:15,520 --> 01:52:16,520
Maybe.

1559
01:52:39,440 --> 01:52:40,600
Welcome again.

1560
01:52:50,080 --> 01:52:51,080
Here.

1561
01:52:55,120 --> 01:52:56,040
Nice.

1562
01:52:56,041 --> 01:52:57,720
Enjoy.

1563
01:53:00,000 --> 01:53:01,000
Mother.

1564
01:53:02,000 --> 01:53:03,000
Thanks daughter.

1565
01:53:19,160 --> 01:53:20,160
Thanks.

1566
01:53:21,200 --> 01:53:22,360
Enjoy.

1567
01:53:34,400 --> 01:53:36,800
On the exact day of your divorce,

1568
01:53:37,760 --> 01:53:38,960
we invited you

1569
01:53:46,240 --> 01:53:47,680
as if rubbing it in

1570
01:53:51,040 --> 01:53:54,320
My brother is just talking
nonsense because he’s nervous.

1571
01:53:57,760 --> 01:53:58,760
No,

1572
01:53:58,880 --> 01:54:00,560
that’s my boy’s normal state,

1573
01:54:00,920 --> 01:54:04,680
he always says nonsense like that…

1574
01:54:11,040 --> 01:54:12,400
He's fun.

1575
01:54:26,360 --> 01:54:27,560
Go ahead.

1576
01:54:28,960 --> 01:54:29,960
Now?

1577
01:54:30,280 --> 01:54:31,280
I mean..

1578
01:54:44,000 --> 01:54:45,000
Love

1579
01:54:45,600 --> 01:54:47,760
is the most beautiful
treasure bestowed upon us by God

1580
01:54:50,800 --> 01:54:52,240
Once a person sees that treasure,

1581
01:54:55,080 --> 01:54:57,760
once his eyes are dazzled by its light,

1582
01:54:58,920 --> 01:55:00,640
cannot see anything else.

1583
01:55:07,080 --> 01:55:08,520
He cannot look anywhere else

1584
01:55:10,040 --> 01:55:11,800
From then on, he
searches for it everywhere.

1585
01:55:17,240 --> 01:55:18,240
Only it…

1586
01:55:25,800 --> 01:55:27,320
Because he knows that without it,

1587
01:55:28,480 --> 01:55:30,560
his heart will remain poor
and lonely in this world.

1588
01:55:34,960 --> 01:55:36,160
How lucky these young people

1589
01:55:36,760 --> 01:55:39,640
are that their hearts have not
remained poor, that they have found love.

1590
01:55:40,440 --> 01:55:45,680
And it falls to us to button up our
coats before love and support them.

1591
01:55:48,840 --> 01:55:49,840
In short…

1592
01:55:50,280 --> 01:55:52,480
By God’s command and the Prophet’s word,

1593
01:55:52,760 --> 01:55:54,240
we ask for your daughter Çiçek’s hand

1594
01:55:54,920 --> 01:55:56,720
for our son Malik.

1595
01:55:57,200 --> 01:55:58,320
Thanks Mr. Ateş.

1596
01:56:17,000 --> 01:56:19,160
We have no buttons here to fasten,

1597
01:56:26,440 --> 01:56:29,320
but we have great respect for love.

1598
01:56:34,000 --> 01:56:35,120
So,

1599
01:56:37,400 --> 01:56:38,400
I give her gladly.

1600
01:57:04,480 --> 01:57:06,240
Sure, Aunt Binnaz.

1601
01:57:34,280 --> 01:57:35,280
Tanks Mr.Ateş.

1602
01:57:37,480 --> 01:57:39,040
It doesn't cut.

1603
01:57:47,720 --> 01:57:50,240
May God bring it to
completion Congratulations!

1604
01:58:04,960 --> 01:58:07,080
Thank you so much.

1605
01:58:07,120 --> 01:58:08,120
Congrats.

1606
01:58:10,360 --> 01:58:12,200
Why did you bother?

1607
01:58:17,080 --> 01:58:18,560
Thank you so much.

1608
01:58:59,560 --> 01:59:03,080
Singing folk songs suits you better
than sitting around all glum like this

1609
01:59:03,640 --> 01:59:04,640
That’s a proven fact…

1610
01:59:09,520 --> 01:59:10,720
Welcome.

1611
01:59:20,920 --> 01:59:22,200
I think you should try this…

1612
01:59:22,880 --> 01:59:24,480
For smiling solutions.

1613
01:59:25,240 --> 01:59:26,400
No thanks.

1614
01:59:30,120 --> 01:59:31,800
Do you want to talk, then?

1615
01:59:33,880 --> 01:59:37,320
Forget it. No need for bad topics.

1616
01:59:38,320 --> 01:59:39,320
Why did you come,

1617
01:59:39,600 --> 01:59:40,840
is everything all right?

1618
01:59:42,160 --> 01:59:43,160
Well…

1619
01:59:43,280 --> 01:59:44,720
depends how you look at it.

1620
01:59:45,760 --> 01:59:47,840
I came to check on
Mercan before the divorce.

1621
01:59:48,840 --> 01:59:49,880
Is she around?

1622
01:59:51,760 --> 01:59:53,640
She and Ateş went to the asking ceremony.

1623
01:59:55,640 --> 01:59:57,200
Honestly, good for them.

1624
01:59:58,160 --> 02:00:00,640
Even in this state, they’re
still doing things for others.

1625
02:00:02,400 --> 02:00:05,120
I think they really
understood what love is.

1626
02:00:07,720 --> 02:00:08,720
True

1627
02:00:09,320 --> 02:00:10,320
Right.

1628
02:00:14,680 --> 02:00:18,560
Some people understand it very wrong…

1629
02:00:22,040 --> 02:00:23,720
and makes a mistake.

1630
02:00:25,640 --> 02:00:27,520
To protect the one he loves.

1631
02:00:29,080 --> 02:00:30,640
He finds excuses for himself

1632
02:00:31,560 --> 02:00:33,880
He lives behind that excuses.

1633
02:00:35,360 --> 02:00:36,360
Then one day

1634
02:00:38,520 --> 02:00:40,080
all the excuses have flown away,

1635
02:00:43,960 --> 02:00:44,960
all that’s left behind

1636
02:00:46,640 --> 02:00:47,720
is plain evil…

1637
02:00:48,520 --> 02:00:51,160
and your own regret.

1638
02:00:56,840 --> 02:00:59,520
I’m glad you saw Aslı’s true face.

1639
02:01:02,440 --> 02:01:03,840
How do you know?

1640
02:01:04,920 --> 02:01:05,920
I can tell.

1641
02:01:07,560 --> 02:01:09,840
I was just waiting so
you could tell me at ease…

1642
02:01:14,040 --> 02:01:15,200
Listen to me, try this.

1643
02:01:15,480 --> 02:01:16,880
This won’t leave you regretting it,

1644
02:01:17,720 --> 02:01:18,920
it’ll make you happy.

1645
02:01:19,400 --> 02:01:21,200
I’m a künefe kind of man.

1646
02:01:21,480 --> 02:01:23,240
We won’t break your heart, of course…

1647
02:01:30,760 --> 02:01:33,080
Then one day, you buy me künefe.

1648
02:01:33,680 --> 02:01:34,680
Sure.

1649
02:01:37,840 --> 02:01:38,840
Bye.

1650
02:01:39,000 --> 02:01:40,000
Bye.

1651
02:02:18,400 --> 02:02:20,560
We should ask your excuse now.

1652
02:02:20,720 --> 02:02:21,880
Oh no… I won’t let you leave

1653
02:02:22,080 --> 02:02:25,160
until you eat my stuffed cabbage rolls.

1654
02:02:25,200 --> 02:02:26,240
Sit down.

1655
02:02:28,480 --> 02:02:29,480
Go ahead.

1656
02:02:41,840 --> 02:02:43,960
They’re wonderful,
Binnaz sister, thank you.

1657
02:02:46,160 --> 02:02:47,320
Enjoy it.

1658
02:02:51,080 --> 02:02:52,160
Truly delicious.

1659
02:02:53,080 --> 02:02:54,360
But we really should go now…

1660
02:02:54,920 --> 02:02:56,080
Don’t go!

1661
02:02:56,120 --> 02:02:57,800
Where are you going?

1662
02:02:57,920 --> 02:02:59,880
There’s pastry too!

1663
02:03:00,160 --> 02:03:02,040
I made it with my own hands…

1664
02:03:02,520 --> 02:03:04,440
You can't go.

1665
02:03:05,080 --> 02:03:09,040
Thank you, Binnaz sister,
but we really need to make it-

1666
02:03:09,520 --> 02:03:13,880
Maybe it would be better if you didn’t.

1667
02:03:16,440 --> 02:03:19,040
Anyway, while you eat this pastry,

1668
02:03:19,520 --> 02:03:21,240
I'll say something.

1669
02:03:21,840 --> 02:03:23,240
Just listen to me a bit.

1670
02:03:33,080 --> 02:03:36,880
Trouble and hardship are the yeast of love.

1671
02:03:37,720 --> 02:03:39,720
By enduring them

1672
02:03:40,280 --> 02:03:43,920
by putting your chest up
against the waves again and again,

1673
02:03:43,960 --> 02:03:45,600
love grows stronger, it multiplies.

1674
02:03:47,440 --> 02:03:52,280
Parting and going on different
paths is the easiest thing…

1675
02:03:53,560 --> 02:03:56,920
But when the sea rises

1676
02:03:57,960 --> 02:04:00,600
when the day darkens,

1677
02:04:01,680 --> 02:04:03,680
when the bitter cold sets in,

1678
02:04:04,000 --> 02:04:07,080
you must not let go of the one you love.

1679
02:04:07,680 --> 02:04:08,680
Yeah.

1680
02:04:09,760 --> 02:04:12,480
Look, these two didn’t.

1681
02:04:23,160 --> 02:04:24,160
Mom,

1682
02:04:25,440 --> 02:04:27,520
you just described what I did too…

1683
02:04:29,680 --> 02:04:31,160
Mrs. Mercan, Mr. Ateş

1684
02:04:33,440 --> 02:04:35,160
I also put my chest

1685
02:04:37,120 --> 02:04:39,680
before obstacles to be
reunited with my Zehra.

1686
02:04:40,760 --> 02:04:41,800
When the day darkened,

1687
02:04:43,120 --> 02:04:44,120
I lit it up,

1688
02:04:45,600 --> 02:04:46,600
when the cold came,

1689
02:04:48,040 --> 02:04:49,160
I lit the fire

1690
02:04:49,600 --> 02:04:52,080
of my love that very instant,

1691
02:04:54,640 --> 02:04:55,920
when the sea rose,

1692
02:04:57,840 --> 02:05:01,040
I took my Zehra and hid her in my bosom…

1693
02:05:01,480 --> 02:05:03,720
What pain we suffered…

1694
02:05:15,320 --> 02:05:17,320
Thank you for everything

1695
02:05:18,280 --> 02:05:19,280
We really

1696
02:05:19,400 --> 02:05:20,600
should go now

1697
02:05:21,280 --> 02:05:22,840
Thank you for everything.

1698
02:05:22,960 --> 02:05:24,120
Excuse us.

1699
02:05:25,040 --> 02:05:26,720
Congratulations again,

1700
02:05:26,880 --> 02:05:28,160
Thanks for coming.

1701
02:05:29,640 --> 02:05:30,760
Thanks.

1702
02:05:31,520 --> 02:05:32,920
Dear Çiçek…

1703
02:05:37,040 --> 02:05:39,080
Congratulations

1704
02:05:41,160 --> 02:05:42,320
Thank you

1705
02:05:45,080 --> 02:05:47,160
Here, Mrs. Mercan.

1706
02:05:48,360 --> 02:05:49,480
Goodbye.

1707
02:05:49,720 --> 02:05:51,440
Thanks again.

1708
02:06:08,360 --> 02:06:09,400
What’s taking him so long?

1709
02:06:10,480 --> 02:06:11,480
He’ll come.

1710
02:06:13,640 --> 02:06:14,640
There he is now…

1711
02:06:22,960 --> 02:06:23,960
Everything’s set.

1712
02:06:24,640 --> 02:06:26,120
I placed the smuggled goods.

1713
02:06:26,800 --> 02:06:28,440
The anonymous tip call is good to go too.

1714
02:06:28,600 --> 02:06:30,000
The plan is running like clockwork.

1715
02:06:33,680 --> 02:06:34,840
Whose son are you, huh?

1716
02:06:37,720 --> 02:06:38,760
I told you.

1717
02:06:39,160 --> 02:06:40,160
I told you.

1718
02:06:41,560 --> 02:06:42,920
I said Burak would handle it.

1719
02:06:43,720 --> 02:06:44,960
Honestly, I didn’t expect this.

1720
02:06:45,440 --> 02:06:46,440
Well done.
Thanks.

1721
02:06:49,960 --> 02:06:51,000
Hear me out Burak.

1722
02:06:51,920 --> 02:06:53,040
Let this work out

1723
02:06:53,320 --> 02:06:54,560
ask me for whatever you want.

1724
02:06:55,640 --> 02:06:57,560
Let’s just tighten the
noose around Ateş’s neck…

1725
02:07:17,920 --> 02:07:19,640
We need to leave soon.

1726
02:07:20,880 --> 02:07:23,080
All right, we’ll go, don’t
worry, you won’t be late!

1727
02:07:27,400 --> 02:07:28,520
Something going on with you?

1728
02:07:30,360 --> 02:07:32,000
I did something without asking you.

1729
02:07:33,280 --> 02:07:34,280
What did you do?

1730
02:07:41,600 --> 02:07:42,600
Hello…

1731
02:07:45,840 --> 02:07:46,840
Okay.

1732
02:07:47,880 --> 02:07:49,320
Thank you very much.

1733
02:07:53,080 --> 02:07:54,120
What’s happening?

1734
02:07:55,560 --> 02:07:56,560
Ateş,

1735
02:07:57,400 --> 02:07:58,400
I...

1736
02:08:10,320 --> 02:08:11,960
What are you doing here?

1737
02:08:14,200 --> 02:08:15,240
I did it.

1738
02:08:16,160 --> 02:08:17,400
I instructed my lawyer

1739
02:08:17,600 --> 02:08:19,520
and said I wasn’t pressing charges.

1740
02:08:21,240 --> 02:08:22,240
Why

1741
02:08:23,200 --> 02:08:25,000
I didn’t want it to drag on.

1742
02:08:25,280 --> 02:08:26,280
Let it end now,

1743
02:08:27,400 --> 02:08:29,600
Besides, compared to what
my own family has done,

1744
02:08:29,880 --> 02:08:31,280
what are the things I went through?

1745
02:08:32,280 --> 02:08:33,440
No one is innocent.

1746
02:08:34,600 --> 02:08:36,560
We’ve already come to the end of the road.

1747
02:08:37,040 --> 02:08:39,440
Aslı won’t see me as a threat anymore.

1748
02:08:40,200 --> 02:08:41,320
She’s done with me…

1749
02:08:45,640 --> 02:08:46,640
Come with me.

1750
02:09:05,800 --> 02:09:07,440
It happened.

1751
02:09:09,040 --> 02:09:11,120
We didn’t let go of each other’s hands.

1752
02:09:12,000 --> 02:09:13,560
We did it, right…

1753
02:09:13,880 --> 02:09:16,240
It was a little hard,

1754
02:09:17,120 --> 02:09:18,320
but we didn’t give up.

1755
02:09:18,480 --> 02:09:19,480
We did it.

1756
02:09:26,920 --> 02:09:27,920
Aunt Binnaz

1757
02:09:29,880 --> 02:09:31,120
Mother Binnaz,

1758
02:09:33,800 --> 02:09:34,800
you trusted me,

1759
02:09:35,600 --> 02:09:36,920
you accepted me into your family.

1760
02:09:37,240 --> 02:09:38,240
Mother Binnaz

1761
02:09:39,080 --> 02:09:42,040
I know what family means to you.

1762
02:09:43,760 --> 02:09:45,160
Don't worry.

1763
02:09:49,200 --> 02:09:50,840
I will take very good care of your flower

1764
02:09:52,680 --> 02:09:53,880
I will never upset her,

1765
02:09:54,240 --> 02:09:55,520
never let her wither,

1766
02:09:56,760 --> 02:09:58,000
I swear it to you.

1767
02:10:05,360 --> 02:10:06,480
It’s Berat!

1768
02:10:06,520 --> 02:10:08,536
He disappeared who knows what
he’s chasing after again…

1769
02:10:08,560 --> 02:10:09,920
Okay, I'll get it.

1770
02:10:30,760 --> 02:10:31,760
Mother…?

1771
02:10:33,440 --> 02:10:34,440
What are you doing here?

1772
02:11:13,800 --> 02:11:14,800
Aslı?

1773
02:11:16,200 --> 02:11:17,200
My daughter!

1774
02:11:19,360 --> 02:11:20,360
My daughter!

1775
02:11:22,760 --> 02:11:24,080
Thank God!

1776
02:11:25,920 --> 02:11:28,080
So Ateş came to his
senses and changed his mind.

1777
02:11:28,960 --> 02:11:31,160
What I said must have had an effect…

1778
02:11:31,760 --> 02:11:32,760
It wasn’t Ateş.

1779
02:11:33,720 --> 02:11:35,040
Mercan got me out.

1780
02:11:35,640 --> 02:11:36,640
What

1781
02:11:36,680 --> 02:11:37,680
Mercan?

1782
02:11:41,200 --> 02:11:42,520
Mercan did, yes.

1783
02:11:46,400 --> 02:11:47,880
But that’s not enough

1784
02:11:49,840 --> 02:11:51,680
You are going to fall at Mercan’s feet

1785
02:11:51,960 --> 02:11:53,120
and apologize.

1786
02:12:05,200 --> 02:12:06,200
Ateş,

1787
02:12:06,360 --> 02:12:07,880
ou acted without asking me, Mercan.

1788
02:12:13,120 --> 02:12:14,400
If she doesn’t apologize,

1789
02:12:15,120 --> 02:12:18,480
I’ll do everything I can
to send her back inside.

1790
02:12:21,920 --> 02:12:22,920
Ateş— Müzeyyen mother,

1791
02:12:26,240 --> 02:12:27,560
I’ve said my final word.

1792
02:12:39,000 --> 02:12:41,240
Either your daughter apologizes,

1793
02:12:42,800 --> 02:12:44,520
or she goes back to prison.

1794
02:12:45,400 --> 02:12:46,560
Believe me, I’ll do it.

1795
02:12:57,120 --> 02:12:58,120
My daughter

1796
02:13:03,640 --> 02:13:04,640
I’m sorry.

1797
02:13:10,560 --> 02:13:11,560
Kneel.

1798
02:13:16,120 --> 02:13:17,120
Ateş!
She will kneel.

1799
02:13:55,840 --> 02:13:56,880
I’m sorry.

1800
02:14:01,800 --> 02:14:02,800
I’m sorry.

1801
02:14:03,320 --> 02:14:04,560
Louder!

1802
02:14:04,960 --> 02:14:06,480
Looking straight into her eyes.

1803
02:14:25,720 --> 02:14:26,800
I’m sorry.

1804
02:14:39,200 --> 02:14:41,360
She will get the hell out of this mansion.

1805
02:14:55,960 --> 02:14:57,560
What was the point of that?

1806
02:14:58,320 --> 02:14:59,560
There was every point.

1807
02:15:01,800 --> 02:15:04,080
What meaning does an apology
have if it isn’t sincere?

1808
02:15:06,200 --> 02:15:07,400
It shouldn’t be that easy.

1809
02:15:09,160 --> 02:15:11,560
Even the fact that she’s
still living here is too much.

1810
02:15:13,440 --> 02:15:14,920
She’ll leave as soon as possible.

1811
02:15:15,360 --> 02:15:16,720
If it weren’t for Müzeyyen mother,

1812
02:15:17,360 --> 02:15:18,840
there would have been much different.

1813
02:15:19,680 --> 02:15:20,720
She should pray for you.

1814
02:15:25,080 --> 02:15:26,080
Anyway...
Okay.

1815
02:15:26,600 --> 02:15:28,160
Let it end and be done with.

1816
02:15:40,640 --> 02:15:43,240
Has the time come?

1817
02:15:51,640 --> 02:15:52,800
Let’s go

1818
02:16:00,280 --> 02:16:01,360
I’ll wait outside

1819
02:16:09,480 --> 02:16:10,920
It’s all ending now.

1820
02:17:17,440 --> 02:17:18,440
Let’s not go.

1821
02:17:21,480 --> 02:17:22,480
What?

1822
02:17:22,520 --> 02:17:23,520
Let’s not go.

1823
02:17:24,160 --> 02:17:25,320
I don’t want to get divorced.

1824
02:17:28,240 --> 02:17:29,240
Ateş?

1825
02:17:30,080 --> 02:17:31,080
Mercan,

1826
02:17:32,080 --> 02:17:33,120
Don’t be stubborn.

1827
02:17:34,480 --> 02:17:35,800
I know you don’t want it either.

1828
02:17:37,280 --> 02:17:38,400
We are not getting divorced.

1829
02:17:39,680 --> 02:17:41,320
Did you just decide that on your own now?

1830
02:17:41,480 --> 02:17:43,160
I decided it.

1831
02:17:47,160 --> 02:17:49,720
Ateş, come on, let’s go.
We’ll be late to court.

1832
02:17:50,280 --> 02:17:51,280
Mercan

1833
02:17:55,200 --> 02:17:56,360
I don’t want to get divorced.

1834
02:18:00,680 --> 02:18:01,680
Then

1835
02:18:02,120 --> 02:18:03,440
I’ll go by myself.

1836
02:18:05,680 --> 02:18:06,680
Mercan

1837
02:18:07,480 --> 02:18:08,480
Mercan

1838
02:18:18,800 --> 02:18:19,800
Mercan

1839
02:18:22,720 --> 02:18:23,720
Mercan, stop!

1840
02:18:24,480 --> 02:18:25,480
Mercan, stop!

1841
02:18:27,000 --> 02:18:28,000
Mercan, get back here!

1842
02:18:30,160 --> 02:18:31,160
Mercan, get back here!

1843
02:18:33,920 --> 02:18:34,920
Mercan…

1844
02:18:35,640 --> 02:18:36,640
Mercan, stop!

1845
02:18:37,080 --> 02:18:37,600
Stop!

1846
02:18:37,920 --> 02:18:38,920
Let go, Ateş…

1847
02:18:39,000 --> 02:18:40,000
Mercan, stop!
Let go

1848
02:18:40,760 --> 02:18:42,160
They won’t allow it

1849
02:18:42,600 --> 02:18:44,640
And you’ll be the one who suffers most.

1850
02:18:44,880 --> 02:18:48,000
I wish they had let us be happy.

1851
02:18:50,120 --> 02:18:51,120
How will this work?

1852
02:18:52,320 --> 02:18:54,920
When you look at me, won’t you
remember everything that happened?

1853
02:18:55,320 --> 02:18:56,320
Fine,

1854
02:18:56,560 --> 02:18:59,280
we will never forget our pain, our past.

1855
02:18:59,920 --> 02:19:01,640
Maybe sometimes we’ll shut down inside.

1856
02:19:01,680 --> 02:19:02,680
So what?

1857
02:19:03,160 --> 02:19:04,960
Fine, there’s hatred all around us.

1858
02:19:05,240 --> 02:19:06,400
We won’t be able to defeat it

1859
02:19:06,680 --> 02:19:08,520
it will always stay
there, that much is clear.

1860
02:19:09,240 --> 02:19:10,960
Let their hatred go to hell.

1861
02:19:11,000 --> 02:19:13,240
Maybe every chance it
gets, it’ll try to wound us.

1862
02:19:14,120 --> 02:19:15,360
Then let me go

1863
02:19:15,520 --> 02:19:17,440
I don’t want to hurt you.

1864
02:19:17,880 --> 02:19:19,960
I don’t want to make you unhappy.

1865
02:19:20,600 --> 02:19:21,600
Mercan

1866
02:19:22,680 --> 02:19:25,880
Because of you, our whole lives will
be a struggle. I understand that now…

1867
02:19:27,280 --> 02:19:29,520
Sometimes we’ll get tired…
Sometimes we’ll give up.

1868
02:19:30,000 --> 02:19:32,656
There will be times when we say we
can’t make it to the end of this road.

1869
02:19:32,680 --> 02:19:34,376
One of us will collapse.
The other will pick them up.

1870
02:19:34,400 --> 02:19:35,400
Do you understand me?

1871
02:19:38,120 --> 02:19:39,120
And if we fall,

1872
02:19:40,120 --> 02:19:41,440
do we fall together too?

1873
02:19:44,760 --> 02:19:45,800
We’ll cry,

1874
02:19:48,920 --> 02:19:49,920
we’ll laugh,

1875
02:19:51,480 --> 02:19:52,480
we’ll get angry.

1876
02:19:54,000 --> 02:19:55,360
But whatever happens

1877
02:19:56,560 --> 02:19:57,800
let it happen together, Mercan.

1878
02:20:01,160 --> 02:20:02,720
You are the most precious thing I have.

1879
02:20:04,120 --> 02:20:05,360
I will make you very happy.

1880
02:20:09,000 --> 02:20:10,800
But if I fail…

1881
02:20:13,080 --> 02:20:14,880
would you still accept
being unhappy with me?

1882
02:22:23,200 --> 02:22:24,600
If we’re going to be unhappy,

1883
02:22:25,440 --> 02:22:26,480
let’s be unhappy together.

1884
02:22:28,040 --> 02:22:29,160
I love you.

1885
02:22:30,240 --> 02:22:31,800
I love you so much.

1886
02:22:32,520 --> 02:22:33,880
I love you so much

1887
02:22:34,200 --> 02:22:35,200
so much!

1888
02:22:43,640 --> 02:22:44,640
So, so much!
